235bool configuration_impl::load(const std::string &_name) {
236 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(mutex_);
237 if (is_loaded_)
238 return true;
239
240 // Environment
241 char *its_env;
242
243 // Predefine file / folder
244 std::string its_file(VSOMEIP_DEFAULT_CONFIGURATION_FILE); // configuration file
245 std::string its_folder(VSOMEIP_DEFAULT_CONFIGURATION_FOLDER); // configuration folder
246
247 if (!path_.empty()) {
248 if (utility::is_file(path_)) {
249 its_file = path_;
250 its_folder = "";
251 } else {
252 its_file = "";
253 its_folder = path_;
254 }
255 }
256
257 // Override with local file / folder (if existing)
258 std::string its_local_file(VSOMEIP_LOCAL_CONFIGURATION_FILE);
259 if (utility::is_file(its_local_file)) {
260 its_file = its_local_file;
261 }
262
263 std::string its_local_folder(VSOMEIP_LOCAL_CONFIGURATION_FOLDER);
264 if (utility::is_folder(its_local_folder)) {
265 its_folder = its_local_folder;
266 }
267
268 // Override with path from environment (if existing)
269 std::string its_named_configuration(VSOMEIP_ENV_CONFIGURATION);
270 its_named_configuration += "_" + _name;
271
272 its_env = getenv(its_named_configuration.c_str());
273 if (nullptr == its_env)
274 its_env = getenv(VSOMEIP_ENV_CONFIGURATION);
275 if (nullptr != its_env) {
276 if (utility::is_file(its_env)) {
277 its_file = its_env;
278 its_folder = "";
279 } else if (utility::is_folder(its_env)) {
280 its_folder = its_env;
281 its_file = "";
282 }
283 }
284
285 std::set<std::string> its_input;
286 if (its_file != "") {
287 its_input.insert(its_file);
288 }
289 if (its_folder != "") {
290 its_input.insert(its_folder);
291#if defined(__linux__) || defined(ANDROID) || defined(__QNX__)
292 // load security configuration files from UID_GID sub folder if existing
293 std::stringstream its_security_config_folder;
294 its_security_config_folder << its_folder << "/" << getuid() << "_" << getgid();
295 if (utility::is_folder(its_security_config_folder.str())) {
296 its_input.insert(its_security_config_folder.str());
297 }
298#endif
299 }
300
301 // Determine standard configuration file
302 its_env = getenv(VSOMEIP_ENV_MANDATORY_CONFIGURATION_FILES);
303 if (nullptr != its_env) {
304 std::string its_temp(its_env);
305 set_mandatory(its_temp);
306 } else {
307 set_mandatory(VSOMEIP_MANDATORY_CONFIGURATION_FILES);
308 }
309
310 // Start reading
311 std::set<std::string> its_failed;
312
313 std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point begin = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
314 std::vector<configuration_element> its_mandatory_elements;
315 std::vector<configuration_element> its_optional_elements;
316
317 // Dummy initialization; maybe we'll find no logging configuration
318 logger::logger_impl::init(shared_from_this());
319
320 // Look for the standard configuration file
321 read_data(its_input, its_mandatory_elements, its_failed, true);
322 load_data(its_mandatory_elements, true, false);
323
324 // If the configuration is incomplete, this is the routing manager configuration or
325 // the routing is yet unknown, read the full set of configuration files
326 if (its_mandatory_elements.empty() ||
327 _name == get_routing_host_name() ||
328 "" == get_routing_host_name()) {
329 read_data(its_input, its_optional_elements, its_failed, false);
330 load_data(its_mandatory_elements, false, true);
331 load_data(its_optional_elements, true, true);
332 }
333
334 // Tell, if reading of configuration file(s) failed.
335 // (This may file if the logger configuration is incomplete/missing).
336 for (auto f : its_failed)
337 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Reading of configuration file \""
338 << f << "\" failed. Configuration may be incomplete.";
339
340 // set global unicast address for all services with magic cookies enabled
341 set_magic_cookies_unicast_address();
342
343 std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point end = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
344
345 for (auto i : its_input) {
346 if (utility::is_file(i))
347 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Using configuration file: \"" << i << "\".";
348
349 if (utility::is_folder(i))
350 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Using configuration folder: \"" << i << "\".";
351 }
352
353 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Parsed vsomeip configuration in "
354 << std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::milliseconds>(end - begin).count()
355 << "ms";
356
357 is_loaded_ = true;
358 return is_loaded_;
359}

361#ifndef VSOMEIP_DISABLE_SECURITY
362bool configuration_impl::lazy_load_security(const std::string &_client_host) {
363 bool result(false);
364
365 std::string its_folder = policy_manager_impl::get()->get_policy_extension_path(_client_host);
366 if (!its_folder.empty()) {
367 std::set<std::string> its_input;
368 std::set<std::string> its_failed;
369 std::vector<configuration_element> its_mandatory_elements;
370
371 its_input.insert(its_folder);
372 // load security configuration files from UID_GID sub folder if existing
373 std::string its_security_config_folder = policy_manager_impl::get()->get_security_config_folder(its_folder);
374
375 if (!its_security_config_folder.empty())
376 its_input.insert(its_security_config_folder);
377
378 read_data(its_input, its_mandatory_elements, its_failed, true, true);
379
380 for (const auto& e : its_mandatory_elements) {
381 policy_manager_impl::get()->load(e, true);
382 }
383
384 for (auto f : its_failed)
385 VSOMEIP_WARNING << __func__ << ": Reading of configuration file \""
386 << f << "\" failed. Configuration may be incomplete.";
387
388 result = (its_failed.empty() && !its_mandatory_elements.empty());
389 if (result)
390 policy_manager_impl::get()->set_is_policy_extension_loaded(_client_host, true);
391 }
392
393 return result;
394}
395#endif // !VSOMEIP_DISABLE_SECURITY

405bool configuration_impl::remote_offer_info_add(service_t _service,
406 instance_t _instance,
407 std::uint16_t _port,
408 bool _reliable,
409 bool _magic_cookies_enabled) {
410 bool ret = false;
411 if (!is_loaded_) {
412 VSOMEIP_ERROR << __func__ << " shall only be called after normal"
413 "configuration has been parsed";
414 } else {
415 std::shared_ptr<service> its_service(std::make_shared<service>());
416 its_service->service_ = _service;
417 its_service->instance_ = _instance;
418 its_service->reliable_ = its_service->unreliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
419 _reliable ?
420 its_service->reliable_ = _port :
421 its_service->unreliable_ = _port;
422 its_service->unicast_address_ = default_unicast_;
423 its_service->multicast_address_ = "";
424 its_service->multicast_port_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
425 its_service->protocol_ = "someip";
426
427 {
428 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(services_mutex_);
429 bool updated(false);
430 auto found_service = services_.find(its_service->service_);
431 if (found_service != services_.end()) {
432 auto found_instance = found_service->second.find(its_service->instance_);
433 if (found_instance != found_service->second.end()) {
434 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Updating remote configuration for service ["
435 << std::hex << std::setw(4) << std::setfill('0')
436 << its_service->service_ << "." << its_service->instance_ << "]";
437 if (_reliable) {
438 found_instance->second->reliable_ = its_service->reliable_;
439 } else {
440 found_instance->second->unreliable_ = its_service->unreliable_;
441 }
442 updated = true;
443 }
444 }
445 if (!updated) {
446 services_[_service][_instance] = its_service;
447 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Added new remote configuration for service ["
448 << std::hex << std::setfill('0')
449 << std::setw(4) << its_service->service_ << "."
450 << std::setw(4) << its_service->instance_ << "]";
451 }
452 if (_magic_cookies_enabled) {
453 magic_cookies_[its_service->unicast_address_].insert(its_service->reliable_);
454 }
455 }
456 ret = true;
457 }
458 return ret;
459}
460
461bool configuration_impl::remote_offer_info_remove(service_t _service,
462 instance_t _instance,
463 std::uint16_t _port,
464 bool _reliable,
465 bool _magic_cookies_enabled,
466 bool* _still_offered_remote) {
467 (void)_port;
468 (void)_magic_cookies_enabled;
469 bool ret = false;
470 if (!is_loaded_) {
471 VSOMEIP_ERROR << __func__ << " shall only be called after normal"
472 "configuration has been parsed";
473 } else {
474 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(services_mutex_);
475 auto found_service = services_.find(_service);
476 if (found_service != services_.end()) {
477 auto found_instance = found_service->second.find(_instance);
478 if (found_instance != found_service->second.end()) {
479 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Removing remote configuration for service ["
480 << std::hex << std::setw(4) << std::setfill('0')
481 << _service << "." << _instance << "]";
482 if (_reliable) {
483 found_instance->second->reliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
484 // TODO delete from magic_cookies_map without overwriting
485 // configurations from other services offered on the same port
486 } else {
487 found_instance->second->unreliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
488 }
489 *_still_offered_remote = (
490 found_instance->second->unreliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT ||
491 found_instance->second->reliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT);
492 ret = true;
493 }
494 }
495 }
496 return ret;
497}

499void configuration_impl::read_data(const std::set<std::string> &_input,
500 std::vector<configuration_element> &_elements, std::set<std::string> &_failed,
501 bool _mandatory_only, bool _read_second_level) {
502 for (auto i : _input) {
503 if (utility::is_file(i)) {
504 load_policy_data(i, _elements, _failed, _mandatory_only);
505 } else if (utility::is_folder(i)) {
506 // Use the map to ensure the configuration files are read in
507 // the ascending order of their names. This allows to use
508 // specific configuration file names to overwrite generic
509 // (or generated) parts of the configuration.
510 std::map<std::string, bool> its_names;
511 boost::filesystem::path its_path(i);
512 for (auto j = boost::filesystem::directory_iterator(its_path);
513 j != boost::filesystem::directory_iterator();
514 j++) {
515 if (!boost::filesystem::is_directory(j->path())) {
516 its_names[j->path().string()] = _mandatory_only;
517 } else if(_read_second_level) {
518 //_read_second_level to read the second level folders only after
519 // the start, without this the ECU block
520 std::string name = j->path().string() + "/vsomeip_security.json";
521 if (utility::is_file(name))
522 its_names[name] = true;
523 }
524 }
525
526 for (const auto &n : its_names)
527 load_policy_data(n.first, _elements, _failed, n.second);
528 }
529 }
530}
531
532void configuration_impl::load_policy_data(const std::string &_input,
533 std::vector<configuration_element> &_elements, std::set<std::string> &_failed,
534 bool _mandatory_only) {
535 if (is_mandatory(_input) == _mandatory_only) {
536#ifndef VSOMEIP_DISABLE_SECURITY
537 if (policy_manager_impl::get()->is_policy_extension(_input)) {
538 policy_manager_impl::get()->set_policy_extension_base_path(_input);
539 }
540#endif
541 boost::property_tree::ptree its_tree;
542 try {
543 boost::property_tree::json_parser::read_json(_input, its_tree);
544 _elements.push_back({ _input, its_tree });
545 }
546 catch (boost::property_tree::json_parser_error&) {
547 _failed.insert(_input);
548 }
549 }
550}
551
552bool configuration_impl::load_data(const std::vector<configuration_element> &_elements,
553 bool _load_mandatory, bool _load_optional) {
554 // Load logging configuration data
555 std::set<std::string> its_warnings;
556
557 if (!is_logging_loaded_) {
558 for (const auto& e : _elements)
559 is_logging_loaded_
560 = load_logging(e, its_warnings) || is_logging_loaded_;
561
562 if (is_logging_loaded_) {
563 logger::logger_impl::init(shared_from_this());
564 for (auto w : its_warnings)
565 VSOMEIP_WARNING << w;
566 }
567 }
568
569 bool has_routing(false);
570 bool has_applications(false);
571 if (_load_mandatory) {
572 // Load mandatory configuration data
573 for (const auto& e : _elements) {
574 has_routing = load_routing(e) || has_routing;
575 has_applications = load_applications(e) || has_applications;
576 load_network(e);
577 load_diagnosis_address(e);
578 load_shutdown_timeout(e);
579 load_payload_sizes(e);
580 load_endpoint_queue_sizes(e);
581 load_tcp_restart_settings(e);
582 load_permissions(e);
583 load_security(e);
584 load_tracing(e);
585 load_udp_receive_buffer_size(e);
586 }
587 }
588
589 if (_load_optional) {
590 for (const auto& e : _elements) {
591 load_unicast_address(e);
592 load_netmask(e);
593 load_device(e);
594 load_service_discovery(e);
595 load_npdu_default_timings(e);
596 load_services(e);
597 load_internal_services(e);
598 load_clients(e);
599 load_watchdog(e);
600 load_selective_broadcasts_support(e);
601 load_e2e(e);
602 load_debounce(e);
603 load_acceptances(e);
604 load_secure_services(e);
605 load_partitions(e);
606 load_routing_client_ports(e);
607 load_suppress_events(e);
608 }
609 }
610
611 return is_logging_loaded_ && has_routing && has_applications;
612}
613
614bool configuration_impl::load_logging(
615 const configuration_element &_element, std::set<std::string> &_warnings) {
616 try {
617 auto its_logging = _element.tree_.get_child("logging");
618 for (auto i = its_logging.begin(); i != its_logging.end(); ++i) {
619 std::string its_key(i->first);
620 if (its_key == "console") {
621 if (is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_CONSOLE]) {
622 _warnings.insert("Multiple definitions for logging.console."
623 " Ignoring definition from " + _element.name_);
624 } else {
625 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
626 #ifndef ANDROID
627 has_console_log_ = (its_value == "true");
628 #else
629 has_console_log_ = true;
630 #endif
631 is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_CONSOLE] = true;
632 }
633 } else if (its_key == "file") {
634 if (is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_FILE]) {
635 _warnings.insert("Multiple definitions for logging.file."
636 " Ignoring definition from " + _element.name_);
637 } else {
638 for (auto j : i->second) {
639 std::string its_sub_key(j.first);
640 std::string its_sub_value(j.second.data());
641 if (its_sub_key == "enable") {
642 has_file_log_ = (its_sub_value == "true");
643 } else if (its_sub_key == "path") {
644 logfile_ = its_sub_value;
645 }
646 }
647 is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_FILE] = true;
648 }
649 } else if (its_key == "dlt") {
650 if (is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_DLT]) {
651 _warnings.insert("Multiple definitions for logging.dlt."
652 " Ignoring definition from " + _element.name_);
653 } else {
654 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
655 has_dlt_log_ = (its_value == "true");
656 is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_DLT] = true;
657 }
658 } else if (its_key == "level") {
659 if (is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_LEVEL]) {
660 _warnings.insert("Multiple definitions for logging.level."
661 " Ignoring definition from " + _element.name_);
662 } else {
663 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
664 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(mutex_loglevel_);
665 loglevel_
666 = (its_value == "trace" ?
667 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_VERBOSE :
668 (its_value == "debug" ?
669 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_DEBUG :
670 (its_value == "info" ?
671 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_INFO :
672 (its_value == "warning" ?
673 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_WARNING :
674 (its_value == "error" ?
675 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_ERROR :
676 (its_value == "fatal" ?
677 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_FATAL :
678 vsomeip_v3::logger::level_e::LL_INFO))))));
679 is_configured_[ET_LOGGING_LEVEL] = true;
680 }
681 } else if (its_key == "version") {
682 std::stringstream its_converter;
683 for (auto j : i->second) {
684 std::string its_sub_key(j.first);
685 std::string its_sub_value(j.second.data());
686 if (its_sub_key == "enable") {
687 log_version_ = (its_sub_value == "true");
688 } else if (its_sub_key == "interval") {
689 its_converter << std::dec << its_sub_value;
690 its_converter >> log_version_interval_;
691 }
692 }
693 } else if (its_key == "memory_log_interval") {
694 std::stringstream its_converter;
695 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
696 its_converter >> log_memory_interval_;
697 if (log_memory_interval_ > 0) {
698 log_memory_ = true;
699 }
700 } else if (its_key == "status_log_interval") {
701 std::stringstream its_converter;
702 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
703 its_converter >> log_status_interval_;
704 if (log_status_interval_ > 0) {
705 log_status_ = true;
706 }
707 } else if (its_key == "statistics") {
708 for (auto j : i->second) {
709 std::stringstream its_converter;
710 std::string its_sub_key(j.first);
711 std::string its_sub_value(j.second.data());
712 if (its_sub_key == "interval") {
713 its_converter << std::dec << its_sub_value;
714 its_converter >> statistics_interval_;
715 if (statistics_interval_ > 0) {
716 log_statistics_ = true;
717 }
718 } else if (its_sub_key == "min-frequency") {
719 its_converter << std::dec << its_sub_value;
720 its_converter >> statistics_min_freq_;
721 } else if (its_sub_key == "max-messages") {
722 its_converter << std::dec << its_sub_value;
723 its_converter >> statistics_max_messages_;
724 }
725 }
726 }
727 }
728 } catch (...) {
729 return false;
730 }
731 return true;
732}
733
734bool
735configuration_impl::load_routing(const configuration_element &_element) {
736 try {
737 auto its_routing = _element.tree_.get_child("routing");
738 if (is_configured_[ET_ROUTING]) {
739 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of routing."
740 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
741 } else {
742 routing_.is_enabled_ =
743 its_routing.get_optional<bool>("enabled").get_value_or(routing_.is_enabled_);
744
745 bool is_loaded = load_routing_host(its_routing, _element.name_)
746 && load_routing_guests(its_routing);
747
748 if (!is_loaded) {
749 routing_.host_.name_ = its_routing.data();
750 } else {
751 if (routing_.guests_.unicast_.is_unspecified())
752 routing_.guests_.unicast_ = routing_.host_.unicast_;
753 if (routing_.guests_.ports_.empty())
754 routing_.guests_.ports_[{ ANY_UID, ANY_GID }].emplace(31492, 31999);
755 }
756
757 // Try to validate the port configuration. Check whether a range
758 // contains an even number of ports and whether its starting port
759 // number fits to the configured routing host port. Correct both
760 // cases by reducing the range, if necessary.
761 std::set<std::pair<port_t, port_t> > its_invalid_ranges;
762 std::set<std::pair<port_t, port_t> > its_corrected_ranges;
763 for (auto &ug : routing_.guests_.ports_) {
764 for (auto &r : ug.second) {
765 auto its_pair = std::make_pair(r.first, r.second);
766
767 bool is_even(((r.second - r.first + 1) % 2) == 0);
768
769 // If the routing host port is [un]even, the start number of the
770 // range shall also be [un]even.
771 bool is_matching((r.first % 2) == (routing_.host_.port_ % 2));
772 if (!is_matching) {
773 its_pair.first++;
774 if (is_even)
775 its_pair.second--;
776 } else if (!is_even) {
777 its_pair.second--;
778 }
779
780 if (!is_even || !is_matching) {
781 its_invalid_ranges.insert(r);
782 its_corrected_ranges.insert(its_pair);
783 }
784 }
785
786 for (const auto &r : its_invalid_ranges)
787 ug.second.erase(r);
788 its_invalid_ranges.clear();
789
790 for (const auto &r : its_corrected_ranges)
791 ug.second.insert(r);
792 its_corrected_ranges.clear();
793 }
794 is_configured_[ET_ROUTING] = true;
795 }
796 } catch (...) {
797 return false;
798 }
799 return true;
800}
801
802bool
803configuration_impl::load_routing_host(const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
804 const std::string &_name) {
805
806 try {
807 bool has_uid(false), has_gid(false);
808 uid_t its_uid;
809 gid_t its_gid;
810 auto its_host = _tree.get_child("host");
811 for (auto i = its_host.begin(); i != its_host.end(); ++i) {
812 std::string its_key(i->first);
813 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
814 if (its_key == "name") {
815 routing_.host_.name_ = its_value;
816 } else if (its_key == "uid" || its_key == "gid") {
817 std::stringstream its_converter;
818 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
819 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
820 } else {
821 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
822 }
823 if (its_key == "uid") {
824 its_converter >> its_uid;
825 has_uid = true;
826 } else {
827 its_converter >> its_gid;
828 has_gid = true;
829 }
830 } else if (its_key == "unicast") {
831#if VSOMEIP_BOOST_VERSION < 106600
832 routing_.host_.unicast_
833 = boost::asio::ip::address::from_string(its_value);
834#else
835 routing_.host_.unicast_
836 = boost::asio::ip::make_address(its_value);
837#endif
838 } else if (its_key == "port") {
839 std::stringstream its_converter;
840 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
841 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
842 } else {
843 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
844 }
845 its_converter >> routing_.host_.port_;
846 }
847 }
848
849 if (has_uid && has_gid) {
850 policy_manager_impl::get()->set_routing_credentials(its_uid, its_gid, _name);
851 }
852
853 } catch (...) {
854 return false;
855 }
856 return true;
857}

860configuration_impl::load_routing_guests(const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
861
862 try {
863 auto its_guests = _tree.get_child("guests");
864 for (auto i = its_guests.begin(); i != its_guests.end(); ++i) {
865 std::string its_key(i->first);
866 if (its_key == "unicast") {
867 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
868#if VSOMEIP_BOOST_VERSION < 106600
869 routing_.guests_.unicast_
870 = boost::asio::ip::address::from_string(its_value);
871#else
872 routing_.guests_.unicast_
873 = boost::asio::ip::make_address(its_value);
874#endif
875 } else if (its_key == "ports") {
876 load_routing_guest_ports(i->second);
877 }
878 }
879 } catch (...) {
880 // intentionally left empty
881 }
882 return true;

884
885void
886configuration_impl::load_routing_guest_ports(
887 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
888
889 std::stringstream its_converter;
890
891 for (auto its_range = _tree.begin();
892 its_range != _tree.end(); ++its_range) {
893
894 uid_t its_uid { ANY_UID };
895 gid_t its_gid { ANY_GID };
896 std::set<std::pair<port_t, port_t> > its_ranges;
897
898 try {
899 auto its_uid_value = its_range->second.get_child("uid").data();
900 its_converter.str("");
901 its_converter.clear();
902 its_converter << its_uid_value;
903 its_converter >> (its_uid_value.find("0x") == 0 ? std::hex : std::dec) >> its_uid;
904
905 auto its_gid_value = its_range->second.get_child("gid").data();
906 its_converter.str("");
907 its_converter.clear();
908 its_converter << its_gid_value;
909 its_converter >> (its_gid_value.find("0x") == 0 ? std::hex : std::dec) >> its_gid;
910
911 auto its_ranges_value = its_range->second.get_child("ranges");
912 its_ranges = load_routing_guest_port_range(its_ranges_value);
913 } catch (...) {
914 its_ranges = load_routing_guest_port_range(its_range->second);
915 }
916
917 if (!its_ranges.empty())
918 routing_.guests_.ports_[{ its_uid, its_gid }] = its_ranges;
919 }
920}
921
922std::set< std::pair<port_t, port_t> >
923configuration_impl::load_routing_guest_port_range(
924 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) const {
925
926 std::stringstream its_converter;
927 std::set< std::pair<port_t, port_t> > its_ranges;
928
929 for (auto its_range = _tree.begin();
930 its_range != _tree.end(); ++its_range) {
931
932 port_t its_first_port { 0 };
933 port_t its_last_port { 0 };
934
935 for (auto its_element = its_range->second.begin();
936 its_element != its_range->second.end(); ++its_element) {
937
938 std::string its_key(its_element->first);
939 std::string its_value(its_element->second.data());
940
941 if (!its_value.empty()) {
942 its_converter.str("");
943 its_converter.clear();
944 its_converter << (its_value.find("0x") == 0 ? std::hex : std::dec) << its_value;
945
946 if (its_key == "first") {
947 its_converter >> its_first_port;
948 } else if (its_key == "last") {
949 its_converter >> its_last_port;
950 }
951 }
952 }
953
954 if (its_first_port > 0 && its_last_port > 0)
955 its_ranges.emplace(std::min(its_first_port, its_last_port),
956 std::max(its_first_port, its_last_port));
957 }
958
959 return its_ranges;
960}

987
988void configuration_impl::load_application_data(
989 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree, const std::string &_file_name) {
990 std::string its_name("");
991 client_t its_id(VSOMEIP_CLIENT_UNSET);
992 std::size_t its_max_dispatchers(VSOMEIP_MAX_DISPATCHERS);
993 std::size_t its_max_dispatch_time(VSOMEIP_MAX_DISPATCH_TIME);
994 std::size_t its_io_thread_count(VSOMEIP_IO_THREAD_COUNT);
995 std::size_t its_request_debounce_time(VSOMEIP_REQUEST_DEBOUNCE_TIME);
996 std::map<plugin_type_e, std::set<std::string>> plugins;
997 int its_io_thread_nice_level(VSOMEIP_IO_THREAD_NICE_LEVEL);
998 debounce_configuration_t its_debounces;
999 bool has_session_handling(true);
1000 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1001 std::string its_key(i->first);
1002 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
1003 std::stringstream its_converter;
1004 if (its_key == "name") {
1005 its_name = its_value;
1006 } else if (its_key == "id") {
1007 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
1008 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
1009 } else {
1010 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1011 }
1012 its_converter >> its_id;
1013 } else if (its_key == "max_dispatchers") {
1014 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1015 its_converter >> its_max_dispatchers;
1016 } else if (its_key == "max_dispatch_time") {
1017 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1018 its_converter >> its_max_dispatch_time;
1019 } else if (its_key == "threads") {
1020 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1021 its_converter >> its_io_thread_count;
1022 if (its_io_thread_count == 0) {
1023 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Min. number of threads per application is 1";
1024 its_io_thread_count = 1;
1025 } else if (its_io_thread_count > 255) {
1026 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Max. number of threads per application is 255";
1027 its_io_thread_count = 255;
1028 }
1029 } else if (its_key == "io_thread_nice") {
1030 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1031 its_converter >> its_io_thread_nice_level;
1032 } else if (its_key == "request_debounce_time") {
1033 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1034 its_converter >> its_request_debounce_time;
1035 if (its_request_debounce_time > 10000) {
1036 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Max. request debounce time is 10.000ms";
1037 its_request_debounce_time = 10000;
1038 }
1039 } else if (its_key == "plugins") {
1040 plugins = load_plugins(i->second, its_name);
1041 } else if (its_key == "debounce") {
1042 try {
1043 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
1044 load_service_debounce(j->second, its_debounces);
1045 }
1046 } catch (...) {
1047 // intentionally empty
1048 }
1049 }
1050 else if (its_key == "has_session_handling") {
1051 has_session_handling = (its_value != "false");
1052 }
1053 }
1054 if (its_name != "") {
1055 if (applications_.find(its_name) == applications_.end()) {
1056 if (its_id != VSOMEIP_CLIENT_UNSET) {
1057 if (!is_configured_client_id(its_id)) {
1058 client_identifiers_.insert(its_id);
1059 } else {
1060 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "Multiple applications are configured to use"
1061 << " client identifier " << std::hex << its_id
1062 << ". Ignoring the configuration for application "
1063 << its_name;
1064 its_id = VSOMEIP_CLIENT_UNSET;
1065 }
1066 }
1067
1068 applications_[its_name] = {
1069 its_id,
1070 its_max_dispatchers,
1071 its_max_dispatch_time,
1072 its_io_thread_count,
1073 its_request_debounce_time,
1074 plugins,
1075 its_io_thread_nice_level,
1076 its_debounces
1077 , has_session_handling
1078 };
1079 } else {
1080 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple configurations for application "
1081 << its_name << ". Ignoring a configuration from "
1082 << _file_name;
1083 }
1084 }
1085}
1086
1087std::map<plugin_type_e, std::set<std::string>> configuration_impl::load_plugins(
1088 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
1089 const std::string &_application_name) {
1090 std::map<plugin_type_e, std::set<std::string>> its_plugins;
1091 std::string its_name("");
1092 std::string its_type;
1093 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1094 bool its_configured[ET_MAX] = { 0 };
1095 for (auto l = i->second.begin(); l != i->second.end(); ++l) {
1096 std::string its_inner_key(l->first);
1097 std::string its_inner_value(l->second.data());
1098
1099 if (its_inner_key == "name") {
1100 if (its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_NAME]) {
1101 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of plugins.name."
1102 << " Ignoring definition from " << its_inner_value;
1103 } else {
1104 its_name = its_inner_value;
1105 its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_NAME] = true;
1106 }
1107 } else if (its_inner_key == "type") {
1108 if (its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_TYPE]) {
1109 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of plugins.type."
1110 << " Ignoring definition from " << its_inner_value;
1111 } else {
1112 its_type = its_inner_value;
1113 its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_TYPE] = true;
1114 }
1115 } else if (its_inner_key == "additional") {
1116 if (its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_NAME]) {
1117 const boost::property_tree::ptree &its_additional_tree(l->second);
1118 for (auto m = its_additional_tree.begin(); m!= its_additional_tree.end(); ++m) {
1119 for (auto n = m->second.begin(); n != m->second.end(); ++n) {
1120 std::string its_additional_inner_key(n->first);
1121 std::string its_additional_inner_value(n->second.data());
1122 plugins_additional_[_application_name][its_name]
1123 [its_additional_inner_key] =
1124 its_additional_inner_value;
1125 }
1126 }
1127 }
1128 } else {
1129 //support old config format (type : name)
1130 plugin_config_data_t its_plugin_data = {
1131 its_inner_value, its_inner_key };
1132 add_plugin(its_plugins, its_plugin_data, _application_name);
1133 }
1134 }
1135
1136 if (its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_NAME] && its_configured[ET_PLUGIN_TYPE]) {
1137 plugin_config_data_t its_plugin_data = {
1138 its_name, its_type };
1139 add_plugin(its_plugins, its_plugin_data, _application_name);
1140 }
1141 }
1142
1143 return its_plugins;
1144}
1145
1146void configuration_impl::add_plugin(std::map<plugin_type_e, std::set<std::string>> &_plugins,
1147 const plugin_config_data_t &_plugin_data,
1148 const std::string& _application_name) {
1149
1150#ifdef _WIN32
1151 std::string its_library(_plugin_data.name_);
1152 its_library += ".dll";
1153#else
1154 std::string its_library("lib");
1155 its_library += _plugin_data.name_;
1156 its_library += ".so";
1157#endif
1158
1159 if (_plugin_data.type_ == "application_plugin") {
1160#if defined(__linux__) || defined(ANDROID) || defined(__QNX__)
1161 its_library += ".";
1162 its_library += (VSOMEIP_APPLICATION_PLUGIN_VERSION + '0');
1163#endif
1164 _plugins[plugin_type_e::APPLICATION_PLUGIN].insert(its_library);
1165 } else if (_plugin_data.type_ == "configuration_plugin") {
1166#if defined(__linux__) || defined(ANDROID) || defined(__QNX__)
1167 its_library += ".";
1168 its_library += (VSOMEIP_PRE_CONFIGURATION_PLUGIN_VERSION + '0');
1169#endif
1170 _plugins[plugin_type_e::PRE_CONFIGURATION_PLUGIN].insert(its_library);
1171 } else {
1172 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Unknown plug-in type ("
1173 << _plugin_data.type_ << ") configured for client: "
1174 << _application_name;
1175 }
1176}
1177
1178void configuration_impl::load_tracing(const configuration_element &_element) {
1179 try {
1180 auto its_trace_configuration = _element.tree_.get_child("tracing");
1181 for(auto i = its_trace_configuration.begin();
1182 i != its_trace_configuration.end();
1183 ++i) {
1184 std::string its_key(i->first);
1185 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
1186 if(its_key == "enable") {
1187 if (is_configured_[ET_TRACING_ENABLE]) {
1188 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of tracing.enable."
1189 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1190 } else {
1191 trace_->is_enabled_ = (its_value == "true");
1192 is_configured_[ET_TRACING_ENABLE] = true;
1193 }
1194 } else if (its_key == "sd_enable") {
1195 if (is_configured_[ET_TRACING_SD_ENABLE]) {
1196 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of tracing.sd_enable."
1197 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1198 } else {
1199 trace_->is_sd_enabled_ = (its_value == "true");
1200 is_configured_[ET_TRACING_SD_ENABLE] = true;
1201 }
1202 } else if(its_key == "channels") {
1203 load_trace_channels(i->second);
1204 } else if(its_key == "filters") {
1205 load_trace_filters(i->second);
1206 }
1207 }
1208 } catch (...) {

1251
1252void configuration_impl::load_trace_filter(
1253 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
1254 std::shared_ptr<trace_filter> its_filter = std::make_shared<trace_filter>();
1255 bool has_channel(false);
1256 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1257 std::string its_key = i->first;
1258 if (its_key == "channel") {
1259 std::string its_value;
1260 if (i->second.size() == 0) {
1261 its_value = i->second.data();
1262 its_filter->channels_.push_back(its_value);
1263 } else {
1264 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
1265 its_filter->channels_.push_back(j->second.data());
1266 }
1267 }
1268 has_channel = true;
1269 } else if(its_key == "type") {
1270 std::string its_value = i->second.data();
1271 if (its_value == "negative")
1272 its_filter->ftype_ = vsomeip_v3::trace::filter_type_e::NEGATIVE;
1273 else if (its_value == "header-only")
1274 its_filter->ftype_ = vsomeip_v3::trace::filter_type_e::HEADER_ONLY;
1275 else
1276 its_filter->ftype_ = vsomeip_v3::trace::filter_type_e::POSITIVE;
1277 } else {
1278 load_trace_filter_expressions(i->second, its_key, its_filter);
1279 }
1280 }
1281
1282 if (!has_channel) {
1283 its_filter->channels_.push_back("TC"); // default
1284 }
1285
1286 if (!its_filter->is_range_ || its_filter->matches_.size() > 0) {
1287 trace_->filters_.push_back(its_filter);
1288 }
1289}
1290
1291void configuration_impl::load_trace_filter_expressions(
1292 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
1293 std::string &_criteria,
1294 std::shared_ptr<trace_filter> &_filter) {
1295 if (_criteria == "services") {
1296 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1297 vsomeip_v3::trace::match_t its_match;
1298 load_trace_filter_match(i->second, its_match);
1299 _filter->matches_.push_back(its_match);
1300 }
1301 } else if (_criteria == "methods") {
1302 if (!has_issued_methods_warning_) {
1303 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "\"method\" entry in filter configuration has no effect!";
1304 has_issued_methods_warning_ = true;
1305 }
1306 } else if (_criteria == "clients") {
1307 if (!has_issued_clients_warning_) {
1308 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "\"clients\" entry in filter configuration has no effect!";
1309 has_issued_clients_warning_ = true;
1310 }
1311 } else if (_criteria == "matches") {
1312 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1313 vsomeip_v3::trace::match_t its_match;
1314 load_trace_filter_match(i->second, its_match);
1315 if (i->first == "from") {
1316 _filter->is_range_ = true;
1317 _filter->matches_.insert(_filter->matches_.begin(), its_match);
1318 } else {
1319 if (i->first == "to") _filter->is_range_ = true;
1320 _filter->matches_.push_back(its_match);
1321 }
1322 }
1323 }
1324}
1325
1326void configuration_impl::load_trace_filter_match(
1327 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_data,
1328 vsomeip_v3::trace::match_t &_match) {
1329 std::stringstream its_converter;
1330
1331 if (_data.size() == 0) {
1332 const std::string& its_value(_data.data());
1333 service_t its_service(ANY_SERVICE);
1334 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
1335 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
1336 } else {
1337 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1338 }
1339 its_converter >> its_service;
1340
1341 std::get<0>(_match) = its_service;
1342 std::get<1>(_match) = ANY_INSTANCE;
1343 std::get<2>(_match) = ANY_METHOD;
1344 } else {
1345 std::get<0>(_match) = ANY_SERVICE;
1346 std::get<1>(_match) = ANY_INSTANCE;
1347 std::get<2>(_match) = ANY_METHOD;
1348
1349 for (auto i = _data.begin(); i != _data.end(); ++i) {
1350 std::string its_value;
1351
1352 its_converter.str("");
1353 its_converter.clear();
1354
1355 try {
1356 its_value = i->second.data();
1357 if (its_value == "any") its_value = "0xffff";
1358
1359 if (i->first == "service") {
1360 service_t its_service(ANY_SERVICE);
1361 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
1362 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
1363 } else {
1364 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1365 }
1366 its_converter >> its_service;
1367 std::get<0>(_match) = its_service;
1368 } else if (i->first == "instance") {
1369 instance_t its_instance(ANY_INSTANCE);
1370 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
1371 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
1372 } else {
1373 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1374 }
1375 its_converter >> its_instance;
1376 std::get<1>(_match) = its_instance;
1377 } else if (i->first == "method") {
1378 method_t its_method(ANY_METHOD);
1379 if (its_value.find("0x") == 0) {
1380 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
1381 } else {
1382 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
1383 }
1384 its_converter >> its_method;
1385 std::get<2>(_match) = its_method;
1386 }
1387 } catch (...) {
1388 // Intentionally left empty
1389 }
1390 }
1391 }
1392}

1412
1413void configuration_impl::load_suppress_events_data(
1414 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
1415
1416 //Default everything to ANY, and change with the provided values
1417 service_t its_service(ANY_SERVICE);
1418 instance_t its_instance(ANY_INSTANCE);
1419 event_t its_event(ANY_EVENT);
1420 std::set<event_t> events;
1421
1422 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1423 std::string its_key(i->first);
1424 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
1425 std::stringstream its_converter;
1426
1427 if (its_key == "service") {
1428 its_service = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1429 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
1430 its_instance = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1431 } else if (its_key == "events") {
1432 if (i->second.empty()) { //Single Event
1433 its_event = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1434 events.insert(its_event);
1435 } else { //Multiple Events/Range
1436 events = load_suppress_multiple_events(i->second);
1437 }
1438 }
1439 }
1440
1441 //If no event is present in the configuration, use ANY_EVENT!
1442 if(events.empty())
1443 events.insert(ANY_EVENT);
1444
1445 for(const auto& event : events) {
1446 insert_suppress_events(its_service, its_instance, event);
1447 }
1448}
1449
1450std::set<event_t> configuration_impl::load_suppress_multiple_events(
1451 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
1452
1453 event_t its_first_event(ANY_EVENT);
1454 event_t its_last_event(ANY_EVENT);
1455 event_t its_event(ANY_EVENT);
1456 std::set<event_t> events;
1457
1458 try {
1459 for(auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1460 std::string its_key(i->first);
1461 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
1462
1463 //Extract Single Event from multiple entries
1464 if (i->second.size() == 0) {
1465
1466 if (its_key == "first") { // Range Events
1467 its_first_event = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1468 } else if (its_key == "last") {
1469 its_last_event = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1470
1471 std::set<event_t> range_events = load_range_events(its_first_event, its_last_event);
1472 events.insert(range_events.begin(), range_events.end());
1473 return events;
1474 } else {
1475 //Single Events
1476 its_event = load_suppress_data(its_value);
1477 events.insert(its_event);
1478 }
1479 } else {
1480 //Go down one level in the JSON, recursively
1481 std::set<event_t> range_events = load_suppress_multiple_events(i->second);
1482 events.insert(range_events.begin(), range_events.end());
1483 }
1484 }
1485 } catch (...) {
1486 // intentionally left empty
1487 }
1488 return events;
1489}
1490
1491uint16_t configuration_impl::load_suppress_data(const std::string &_value) const {
1492
1493 std::stringstream its_converter;
1494 uint16_t its_converted = ANY_EVENT;
1495
1496 if (_value == "any") {
1497 its_converted = ANY_EVENT; //use ANY_x
1498 } else if (_value.find("0x") == 0) {
1499 its_converter << std::hex << _value;
1500 } else {
1501 its_converter << std::dec << _value;
1502 }
1503 its_converter >> its_converted;
1504
1505 return its_converted;
1506}
1507
1508std::set<event_t> configuration_impl::load_range_events(event_t _first_event,
1509 event_t _last_event) const {
1510
1511 std::set<event_t> range_events;
1512
1513 if ((_first_event != ANY_EVENT) && (_last_event != ANY_EVENT)) {
1514 for (event_t its_event = _first_event; its_event<=_last_event; its_event++) {
1515 range_events.insert(its_event);
1516 }
1517 }
1518 return range_events;
1519}
1520
1521void configuration_impl::insert_suppress_events(service_t _service,
1522 instance_t _instance, event_t _event) {
1523
1524 suppress_t new_event = {_service, _instance, _event};
1525 suppress_events_.insert(new_event);
1526}
1527
1528bool configuration_impl::check_suppress_events(service_t _service, instance_t _instance,
1529 event_t _event) const {
1530
1531 if (!is_suppress_events_enabled_)
1532 return false;
1533
1534 std::set<suppress_t> event_combinations = {
1535 {_service, _instance, _event},
1536 {_service, _instance, ANY_EVENT},
1537 {_service, ANY_INSTANCE, _event},
1538 {_service, ANY_INSTANCE, ANY_EVENT},
1539 {ANY_SERVICE, _instance, _event},
1540 {ANY_SERVICE, _instance, ANY_EVENT},
1541 {ANY_SERVICE, ANY_INSTANCE, _event}
1542 };
1543
1544 for (const auto &its_event: event_combinations) {
1545 if (suppress_events_.find(its_event) != std::end(suppress_events_))
1546 return true;
1547 }
1548
1549 return false;
1550}
1551
1552void configuration_impl::print_suppress_events(void) const {
1553
1554 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Suppress Event logs size: " << suppress_events_.size();
1555
1556 for (const auto& its_log : suppress_events_) {
1557 VSOMEIP_INFO << std::hex << std::setfill('0')
1558 << "+[" << std::setw(4) << its_log.service
1559 << "." << std::setw(4) << its_log.instance
1560 << "." << its_log.event << "]";
1561 }

1579void configuration_impl::load_netmask(const configuration_element &_element) {
1580 try {
1581 auto its_value = _element.tree_.get_optional<std::string>("netmask");
1582 if (its_value) {
1583 if (is_configured_[ET_NETMASK]) {
1584 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for netmask/prefix."
1585 "Ignoring netmask definition from " << _element.name_;
1586 } else {
1587 netmask_ = netmask_.from_string(*its_value);
1588 is_configured_[ET_NETMASK] = true;
1589 }
1590 }
1591
1592 its_value = _element.tree_.get_optional<std::string>("prefix");
1593 if (its_value) {
1594 if (is_configured_[ET_NETMASK]) {
1595 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for prefix/netmask."
1596 "Ignoring prefix definition from " << _element.name_;
1597 } else {
1598 std::stringstream its_converter;
1599 its_converter << *its_value;
1600 its_converter >> std::dec >> prefix_;
1601
1602 // Convert to netmask as this is used for IPv4.
1603 uint32_t its_netmask = (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()
1604 << (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::digits - prefix_))
1605 & std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
1606 netmask_ = boost::asio::ip::address_v4(its_netmask);
1607
1608 is_configured_[ET_NETMASK] = true;
1609 }
1610 }
1611 } catch (...) {
1612 // intentionally left empty!
1613 }

1646void configuration_impl::load_diagnosis_address(const configuration_element &_element) {

1715
1716void configuration_impl::load_service_discovery(
1717 const configuration_element &_element) {
1718 try {
1719 auto its_service_discovery = _element.tree_.get_child("service-discovery");
1720 for (auto i = its_service_discovery.begin();
1721 i != its_service_discovery.end(); ++i) {
1722 std::string its_key(i->first);
1723 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
1724 std::stringstream its_converter;
1725 if (its_key == "enable") {
1726 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_ENABLE]) {
1727 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.enabled."
1728 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1729 } else {
1730 is_sd_enabled_ = (its_value == "true");
1731 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_ENABLE] = true;
1732 }
1733 } else if (its_key == "multicast") {
1734 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_MULTICAST]) {
1735 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.multicast."
1736 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1737 } else {
1738 sd_multicast_ = its_value;
1739 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_MULTICAST] = true;
1740 }
1741 } else if (its_key == "port") {
1742 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_PORT]) {
1743 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.port."
1744 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1745 } else {
1746 its_converter << its_value;
1747 its_converter >> sd_port_;
1748 if (!sd_port_) {
1749 sd_port_ = VSOMEIP_SD_DEFAULT_PORT;
1750 } else {
1751 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_PORT] = true;
1752 }
1753 }
1754 } else if (its_key == "protocol") {
1755 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_PROTOCOL]) {
1756 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.protocol."
1757 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1758 } else {
1759 sd_protocol_ = its_value;
1760 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_PROTOCOL] = true;
1761 }
1762 } else if (its_key == "initial_delay_min") {
1763 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_INITIAL_DELAY_MIN]) {
1764 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.initial_delay_min."
1765 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1766 } else {
1767 its_converter << its_value;
1768 its_converter >> sd_initial_delay_min_;
1769 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_INITIAL_DELAY_MIN] = true;
1770 }
1771 } else if (its_key == "initial_delay_max") {
1772 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_INITIAL_DELAY_MAX]) {
1773 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.initial_delay_max."
1774 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1775 } else {
1776 its_converter << its_value;
1777 its_converter >> sd_initial_delay_max_;
1778 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_INITIAL_DELAY_MAX] = true;
1779 }
1780 } else if (its_key == "repetitions_base_delay") {
1781 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REPETITION_BASE_DELAY]) {
1782 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.repetition_base_delay."
1783 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1784 } else {
1785 its_converter << its_value;
1786 its_converter >> sd_repetitions_base_delay_;
1787 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REPETITION_BASE_DELAY] = true;
1788 }
1789 } else if (its_key == "repetitions_max") {
1790 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REPETITION_MAX]) {
1791 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.repetition_max."
1792 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1793 } else {
1794 int tmp;
1795 its_converter << its_value;
1796 its_converter >> tmp;
1797 sd_repetitions_max_ = (tmp > std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max()) ?
1798 std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max() :
1799 static_cast<std::uint8_t>(tmp);
1800 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REPETITION_MAX] = true;
1801 }
1802 } else if (its_key == "ttl") {
1803 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL]) {
1804 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.ttl."
1805 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1806 } else {
1807 its_converter << its_value;
1808 its_converter >> sd_ttl_;
1809 // We do _not_ accept 0 as this would mean "STOP OFFER"
1810 if (sd_ttl_ == 0) {
1811 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "TTL=0 is not allowed. Using default ("
1812 << std::dec << VSOMEIP_SD_DEFAULT_TTL << ")";
1813 sd_ttl_ = VSOMEIP_SD_DEFAULT_TTL;
1814 }
1815 else is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL] = true;
1816 }
1817 } else if (its_key == "cyclic_offer_delay") {
1818 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_CYCLIC_OFFER_DELAY]) {
1819 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.cyclic_offer_delay."
1820 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1821 } else {
1822 its_converter << its_value;
1823 its_converter >> sd_cyclic_offer_delay_;
1824 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_CYCLIC_OFFER_DELAY] = true;
1825 }
1826 } else if (its_key == "request_response_delay") {
1827 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REQUEST_RESPONSE_DELAY]) {
1828 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.request_response_delay."
1829 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1830 } else {
1831 its_converter << its_value;
1832 its_converter >> sd_request_response_delay_;
1833 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_REQUEST_RESPONSE_DELAY] = true;
1834 }
1835 } else if (its_key == "offer_debounce_time") {
1836 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_OFFER_DEBOUNCE_TIME]) {
1837 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.offer_debounce."
1838 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1839 } else {
1840 its_converter << its_value;
1841 its_converter >> sd_offer_debounce_time_;
1842 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_OFFER_DEBOUNCE_TIME] = true;
1843 }
1844 } else if (its_key == "ttl_factor_offers") {
1845 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL_FACTOR_OFFERS]) {
1846 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.ttl_factor_offers."
1847 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1848 } else {
1849 load_ttl_factors(i->second, &ttl_factors_offers_);
1850 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL_FACTOR_OFFERS] = true;
1851 }
1852 } else if (its_key == "ttl_factor_subscriptions") {
1853 if (is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL_FACTOR_SUBSCRIPTIONS]) {
1854 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.ttl_factor_subscriptions."
1855 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1856 } else {
1857 load_ttl_factors(i->second, &ttl_factors_subscriptions_);
1858 is_configured_[ET_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_TTL_FACTOR_SUBSCRIPTIONS] = true;
1859 }
1860 } else if (its_key == "max_remote_subscribers") {
1861 if (is_configured_[ET_MAX_REMOTE_SUBSCRIBERS]) {
1862 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for service_discovery.max_remote_subscribers."
1863 " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1864 } else {
1865 int tmp;
1866 its_converter << its_value;
1867 its_converter >> tmp;
1868 max_remote_subscribers_ = (tmp > std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max()) ?
1869 std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max() :
1870 static_cast<std::uint8_t>(tmp);
1871 if (max_remote_subscribers_ == 0) {
1872 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "max_remote_subscribers_ = 0 is not allowed. Using default ("
1873 << std::dec << VSOMEIP_DEFAULT_MAX_REMOTE_SUBSCRIBERS << ")";
1874 max_remote_subscribers_ = VSOMEIP_DEFAULT_MAX_REMOTE_SUBSCRIBERS;
1875 }
1876 is_configured_[ET_MAX_REMOTE_SUBSCRIBERS] = true;
1877 }
1878 }
1879 }
1880 } catch (...) {
1881 }

1884void configuration_impl::load_delays(
1885 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
1886 try {
1887 std::stringstream its_converter;
1888 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
1889 std::string its_key(i->first);
1890 if (its_key == "initial") {
1891 sd_initial_delay_min_ = i->second.get<uint32_t>("minimum");
1892 sd_initial_delay_max_ = i->second.get<uint32_t>("maximum");
1893 } else if (its_key == "repetition-base") {
1894 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
1895 its_converter >> sd_repetitions_base_delay_;
1896 } else if (its_key == "repetition-max") {
1897 int tmp_repetition_max;
1898 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
1899 its_converter >> tmp_repetition_max;
1900 sd_repetitions_max_ =
1901 (tmp_repetition_max
1902 > std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max()) ?
1903 std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max() :
1904 static_cast<std::uint8_t>(tmp_repetition_max);
1905 } else if (its_key == "cyclic-offer") {
1906 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
1907 its_converter >> sd_cyclic_offer_delay_;
1908 } else if (its_key == "cyclic-request") {
1909 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
1910 its_converter >> sd_request_response_delay_;
1911 } else if (its_key == "ttl") {
1912 its_converter << std::dec << i->second.data();
1913 its_converter >> sd_ttl_;
1914 }
1915 its_converter.str("");
1916 its_converter.clear();
1917 }
1918 } catch (...) {
1919 }

1922void configuration_impl::load_npdu_default_timings(const configuration_element &_element) {
1923 const std::string ndt("npdu-default-timings");
1924 const std::string dreq("debounce-time-request");
1925 const std::string dres("debounce-time-response");
1926 const std::string rreq("max-retention-time-request");
1927 const std::string rresp("max-retention-time-response");
1928 try {
1929 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(ndt)) {
1930 if (is_configured_[ET_NPDU_DEFAULT_TIMINGS]) {
1931 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions of " << ndt
1932 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
1933 } else {
1934 for (const auto& e : _element.tree_.get_child(ndt)) {
1935 std::chrono::nanoseconds its_time(0);
1936 try {
1937 its_time = std::chrono::nanoseconds(
1938 std::strtoull(e.second.data().c_str(), NULL, 10)
1939 * 1000000);
1940 } catch (const std::exception&) {
1941 continue;
1942 }
1943 if (e.first.data() == dreq) {
1944 npdu_default_debounce_requ_ = its_time;
1945 } else if (e.first.data() == dres) {
1946 npdu_default_debounce_resp_ = its_time;
1947 } else if (e.first.data() == rreq) {
1948 npdu_default_max_retention_requ_ = its_time;
1949 } else if (e.first.data() == rresp) {
1950 npdu_default_max_retention_resp_ = its_time;
1951 }
1952 }
1953 is_configured_[ET_NPDU_DEFAULT_TIMINGS] = true;
1954 }
1955 }
1956 } catch (...) {
1957 // intentionally left empty
1958 }

1978void configuration_impl::load_servicegroup(

1983 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {

1997 load_service(j->second, its_unicast_address);

2005void configuration_impl::load_service(
2006 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
2007 const std::string &_unicast_address) {
2008 try {
2009 bool is_loaded(true);
2010 bool use_magic_cookies(false);
2011
2012 std::shared_ptr<service> its_service(std::make_shared<service>());
2013 its_service->reliable_ = its_service->unreliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2014 its_service->unicast_address_ = _unicast_address;
2015 its_service->multicast_address_ = "";
2016 its_service->multicast_port_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2017 its_service->protocol_ = "someip";
2018
2019 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2020 std::string its_key(i->first);
2021 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
2022 std::stringstream its_converter;
2023
2024 if (its_key == "unicast") {
2025 its_service->unicast_address_ = its_value;
2026 } else if (its_key == "reliable") {
2027 try {
2028 its_value = i->second.get_child("port").data();
2029 its_converter << its_value;
2030 its_converter >> its_service->reliable_;
2031 } catch (...) {
2032 its_converter << its_value;
2033 its_converter >> its_service->reliable_;
2034 }
2035 if(!its_service->reliable_) {
2036 its_service->reliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2037 }
2038 try {
2039 its_value
2040 = i->second.get_child("enable-magic-cookies").data();
2041 use_magic_cookies = ("true" == its_value);
2042 } catch (...) {
2043
2044 }
2045 } else if (its_key == "unreliable") {
2046 its_converter << its_value;
2047 its_converter >> its_service->unreliable_;
2048 if(!its_service->unreliable_) {
2049 its_service->unreliable_ = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2050 }
2051 } else if (its_key == "multicast") {
2052 try {
2053 its_value = i->second.get_child("address").data();
2054 its_service->multicast_address_ = its_value;
2055 its_value = i->second.get_child("port").data();
2056 its_converter << its_value;
2057 its_converter >> its_service->multicast_port_;
2058 } catch (...) {
2059 }
2060 } else if (its_key == "protocol") {
2061 its_service->protocol_ = its_value;
2062 } else if (its_key == "events") {
2063 load_event(its_service, i->second);
2064 } else if (its_key == "eventgroups") {
2065 load_eventgroup(its_service, i->second);
2066 } else if (its_key == "debounce-times") {
2067 load_npdu_debounce_times_configuration(its_service, i->second);
2068 } else if (its_key == "someip-tp") {
2069 load_someip_tp(its_service, i->second);
2070 } else {
2071 // Trim "its_value"
2072 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2073 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2074 } else {
2075 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2076 }
2077
2078 if (its_key == "service") {
2079 its_converter >> its_service->service_;
2080 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
2081 its_converter >> its_service->instance_;
2082 }
2083 }
2084 }
2085
2086 auto found_service = services_.find(its_service->service_);
2087 if (found_service != services_.end()) {
2088 auto found_instance = found_service->second.find(
2089 its_service->instance_);
2090 if (found_instance != found_service->second.end()) {
2091 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple configurations for service ["
2092 << std::hex << its_service->service_ << "."
2093 << its_service->instance_ << "]";
2094 is_loaded = false;
2095 }
2096 }
2097
2098 if (is_loaded) {
2099 services_[its_service->service_][its_service->instance_] =
2100 its_service;
2101 if (use_magic_cookies) {
2102 magic_cookies_[its_service->unicast_address_].insert(its_service->reliable_);
2103 }
2104
2105 if (its_service->unicast_address_ == default_unicast_) {
2106 // local services
2107 if(its_service->reliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2108 services_by_ip_port_[unicast_.to_string()]
2109 [its_service->reliable_]
2110 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2111 }
2112 if (its_service->unreliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2113 services_by_ip_port_[unicast_.to_string()]
2114 [its_service->unreliable_]
2115 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2116 // This is necessary as all udp server endpoints listen on
2117 // INADDR_ANY instead of a specific address
2118 services_by_ip_port_[boost::asio::ip::address_v4::any().to_string()]
2119 [its_service->unreliable_]
2120 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2121 services_by_ip_port_[boost::asio::ip::address_v6::any().to_string()]
2122 [its_service->unreliable_]
2123 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2124 }
2125 } else {
2126 // remote services
2127 if (its_service->reliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2128 services_by_ip_port_[its_service->unicast_address_]
2129 [its_service->reliable_]
2130 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2131 }
2132 if (its_service->unreliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2133 services_by_ip_port_[its_service->unicast_address_]
2134 [its_service->unreliable_]
2135 [its_service->service_] = its_service;
2136 }
2137 }
2138 }
2139 } catch (...) {
2140 // Intentionally left empty
2141 }
2142}

2144void configuration_impl::load_event(
2145 std::shared_ptr<service> &_service,
2146 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2147 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2148 event_t its_event_id(0);
2149 bool its_is_field(false);
2150 reliability_type_e its_reliability(reliability_type_e::RT_UNKNOWN);
2151 uint32_t its_cycle_value;
2152 std::chrono::milliseconds its_cycle(std::chrono::milliseconds::zero());
2153 bool its_change_resets_cycle(false);
2154 bool its_update_on_change(true);
2155
2156 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
2157 std::string its_key(j->first);
2158 std::string its_value(j->second.data());
2159 if (its_key == "event") {
2160 std::stringstream its_converter;
2161 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2162 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2163 } else {
2164 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2165 }
2166 its_converter >> its_event_id;
2167 } else if (its_key == "is_field") {
2168 its_is_field = (its_value == "true");
2169 } else if (its_key == "is_reliable") {
2170 if (its_value == "true")
2171 its_reliability = reliability_type_e::RT_RELIABLE;
2172 else
2173 its_reliability = reliability_type_e::RT_UNRELIABLE;
2174 } else if (its_key == "cycle") {
2175 std::stringstream its_converter;
2176 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2177 its_converter >> its_cycle_value;
2178 its_cycle = std::chrono::milliseconds(its_cycle_value);
2179 } else if (its_key == "change_resets_cycle") {
2180 its_change_resets_cycle = (its_value == "true");
2181 } else if (its_key == "update_on_change") {
2182 its_update_on_change = (its_value == "true");
2183 }
2184 }
2185
2186 if (its_event_id > 0) {
2187 auto found_event = _service->events_.find(its_event_id);
2188 if (found_event != _service->events_.end()) {
2189 VSOMEIP_INFO << "Multiple configurations for event ["
2190 << std::hex << _service->service_ << "."
2191 << _service->instance_ << "."
2192 << its_event_id << "].";
2193 } else {
2194 // If event reliability type was not configured,
2195 if (its_reliability == reliability_type_e::RT_UNKNOWN) {
2196 if (_service->unreliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2197 its_reliability = reliability_type_e::RT_UNRELIABLE;
2198 } else if (_service->reliable_ != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
2199 its_reliability = reliability_type_e::RT_RELIABLE;
2200 }
2201 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Reliability type for event ["
2202 << std::hex << _service->service_ << "."
2203 << _service->instance_ << "."
2204 << its_event_id << "] was not configured Using : "
2205 << ((its_reliability == reliability_type_e::RT_RELIABLE)
2206 ? "RT_RELIABLE" : "RT_UNRELIABLE");
2207 }
2208
2209 std::shared_ptr<event> its_event = std::make_shared<event>(
2210 its_event_id, its_is_field, its_reliability,
2211 its_cycle, its_change_resets_cycle,
2212 its_update_on_change);
2213 _service->events_[its_event_id] = its_event;
2214 }
2215 }
2216 }
2217}

2219void configuration_impl::load_eventgroup(
2220 std::shared_ptr<service> &_service,
2221 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2222 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2223 std::shared_ptr<eventgroup> its_eventgroup =
2224 std::make_shared<eventgroup>();
2225 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
2226 std::stringstream its_converter;
2227 std::string its_key(j->first);
2228 std::string its_value(j->second.data());
2229 if (its_key == "eventgroup") {
2230 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2231 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2232 } else {
2233 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2234 }
2235 its_converter >> its_eventgroup->id_;
2236 } else if (its_key == "is_multicast") {
2237 std::string its_value(j->second.data());
2238 if (its_value == "true") {
2239 its_eventgroup->multicast_address_ = _service->multicast_address_;
2240 its_eventgroup->multicast_port_ = _service->multicast_port_;
2241 }
2242 } else if (its_key == "multicast") {
2243 try {
2244 std::string its_value = j->second.get_child("address").data();
2245 its_eventgroup->multicast_address_ = its_value;
2246 its_value = j->second.get_child("port").data();
2247 its_converter << its_value;
2248 its_converter >> its_eventgroup->multicast_port_;
2249 } catch (...) {
2250 }
2251 } else if (its_key == "threshold") {
2252 int its_threshold(0);
2253 std::stringstream its_converter;
2254 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2255 its_converter >> std::dec >> its_threshold;
2256 its_eventgroup->threshold_ =
2257 (its_threshold > std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max()) ?
2258 std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max() :
2259 static_cast<uint8_t>(its_threshold);
2260 } else if (its_key == "events") {
2261 for (auto k = j->second.begin(); k != j->second.end(); ++k) {
2262 std::stringstream its_converter;
2263 std::string its_value(k->second.data());
2264 event_t its_event_id(0);
2265 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2266 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2267 } else {
2268 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2269 }
2270 its_converter >> its_event_id;
2271 if (0 < its_event_id) {
2272 std::shared_ptr<event> its_event(nullptr);
2273 auto find_event = _service->events_.find(its_event_id);
2274 if (find_event != _service->events_.end()) {
2275 its_event = find_event->second;
2276 } else {
2277 its_event = std::make_shared<event>(its_event_id,
2278 false, reliability_type_e::RT_UNRELIABLE,
2279 std::chrono::milliseconds::zero(),
2280 false, true);
2281 }
2282 if (its_event) {
2283 its_event->groups_.push_back(its_eventgroup);
2284 its_eventgroup->events_.insert(its_event);
2285 _service->events_[its_event_id] = its_event;
2286 }
2287 }
2288 }
2289 }
2290 }
2291
2292 if (its_eventgroup->id_ > 0) {
2293 _service->eventgroups_[its_eventgroup->id_] = its_eventgroup;
2294 }
2295 }

2298void configuration_impl::load_internal_services(const configuration_element &_element) {
2299 try {
2300 auto optional = _element.tree_.get_child_optional("internal_services");
2301 if (!optional) {
2302 return;
2303 }
2304 auto its_internal_services = _element.tree_.get_child("internal_services");
2305 for (auto found_range = its_internal_services.begin();
2306 found_range != its_internal_services.end(); ++found_range) {
2307 service_instance_range range;
2308 range.first_service_ = 0x0;
2309 range.last_service_ = 0x0;
2310 range.first_instance_ = 0x0;
2311 range.last_instance_ = 0xffff;
2312 for (auto i = found_range->second.begin();
2313 i != found_range->second.end(); ++i) {
2314 if (i->first == "first") {
2315 if (i->second.size() == 0) {
2316 std::stringstream its_converter;
2317 std::string value = i->second.data();
2318 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2319 its_converter >> range.first_service_;
2320 }
2321 for (auto n = i->second.begin();
2322 n != i->second.end(); ++n) {
2323 if (n->first == "service") {
2324 std::stringstream its_converter;
2325 std::string value = n->second.data();
2326 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2327 its_converter >> range.first_service_;
2328 } else if (n->first == "instance") {
2329 std::stringstream its_converter;
2330 std::string value = n->second.data();
2331 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2332 its_converter >> range.first_instance_;
2333 }
2334 }
2335 } else if (i->first == "last") {
2336 if (i->second.size() == 0) {
2337 std::stringstream its_converter;
2338 std::string value = i->second.data();
2339 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2340 its_converter >> range.last_service_;
2341 }
2342 for (auto n = i->second.begin();
2343 n != i->second.end(); ++n) {
2344 if (n->first == "service") {
2345 std::stringstream its_converter;
2346 std::string value = n->second.data();
2347 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2348 its_converter >> range.last_service_;
2349 } else if (n->first == "instance") {
2350 std::stringstream its_converter;
2351 std::string value = n->second.data();
2352 its_converter << std::hex << value;
2353 its_converter >> range.last_instance_;
2354 }
2355 }
2356 }
2357 }
2358 if (range.last_service_ >= range.first_service_) {
2359 if (range.last_instance_ >= range.first_instance_) {
2360 internal_service_ranges_.push_back(range);
2361 }
2362 }
2363 }
2364 } catch (...) {
2365 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "Error parsing internal service range configuration!";
2366 }

2369void configuration_impl::load_clients(const configuration_element &_element) {
2370 try {
2371 auto its_clients = _element.tree_.get_child("clients");
2372 for (auto i = its_clients.begin(); i != its_clients.end(); ++i)
2373 load_client(i->second);
2374 } catch (...) {
2375 // intentionally left empty!
2376 }
2377}
2378
2379void configuration_impl::load_client(const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2380 try {
2381 std::shared_ptr<client> its_client(std::make_shared<client>());
2382 its_client->remote_ports_[true] = std::make_pair(ILLEGAL_PORT, ILLEGAL_PORT);
2383 its_client->remote_ports_[false] = std::make_pair(ILLEGAL_PORT, ILLEGAL_PORT);
2384 its_client->client_ports_[true] = std::make_pair(ILLEGAL_PORT, ILLEGAL_PORT);
2385 its_client->client_ports_[false] = std::make_pair(ILLEGAL_PORT, ILLEGAL_PORT);
2386 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[true] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2387 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[false] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2388 its_client->last_used_client_port_[true] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2389 its_client->last_used_client_port_[false] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2390
2391 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2392 std::string its_key(i->first);
2393 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
2394 std::stringstream its_converter;
2395
2396 if (its_key == "reliable_remote_ports") {
2397 its_client->remote_ports_[true] = load_client_port_range(i->second);
2398 } else if (its_key == "unreliable_remote_ports") {
2399 its_client->remote_ports_[false] = load_client_port_range(i->second);
2400 } else if (its_key == "reliable_client_ports") {
2401 its_client->client_ports_[true] = load_client_port_range(i->second);
2402 } else if (its_key == "unreliable_client_ports") {
2403 its_client->client_ports_[false] = load_client_port_range(i->second);
2404 } else if (its_key == "reliable") {
2405 its_client->ports_[true] = load_client_ports(i->second);
2406 } else if (its_key == "unreliable") {
2407 its_client->ports_[false] = load_client_ports(i->second);
2408 } else {
2409 // Trim "its_value"
2410 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2411 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2412 } else {
2413 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2414 }
2415
2416 if (its_key == "service") {
2417 its_converter >> its_client->service_;
2418 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
2419 its_converter >> its_client->instance_;
2420 }
2421 }
2422 }
2423 clients_.push_back(its_client);
2424 } catch (...) {
2425 }
2426}

2428std::set<uint16_t> configuration_impl::load_client_ports(
2429 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2430 std::set<uint16_t> its_ports;
2431 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2432 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
2433 uint16_t its_port_value;
2434
2435 std::stringstream its_converter;
2436 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2437 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2438 } else {
2439 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2440 }
2441 its_converter >> its_port_value;
2442 its_ports.insert(its_port_value);
2443 }
2444 return its_ports;

2447std::pair<uint16_t,uint16_t> configuration_impl::load_client_port_range(
2448 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2449 std::pair<uint16_t,uint16_t> its_port_range;
2450 uint16_t its_first_port = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2451 uint16_t its_last_port = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2452
2453 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2454 std::string its_key(i->first);
2455 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
2456 std::stringstream its_converter;
2457
2458 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
2459 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
2460 } else {
2461 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
2462 }
2463
2464 if (its_key == "first") {
2465 its_converter >> its_first_port;
2466 } else if (its_key == "last") {
2467 its_converter >> its_last_port;
2468 }
2469 }
2470
2471 if (its_last_port < its_first_port) {
2472 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Port range invalid: first: " << std::dec << its_first_port << " last: " << its_last_port;
2473 its_port_range = std::make_pair(ILLEGAL_PORT, ILLEGAL_PORT);
2474 } else {
2475 its_port_range = std::make_pair(its_first_port, its_last_port);
2476 }
2477
2478 return its_port_range;
2479}

2520
2521void configuration_impl::load_payload_sizes(const configuration_element &_element) {
2522 const std::string payload_sizes("payload-sizes");
2523 const std::string max_local_payload_size("max-payload-size-local");
2524 const std::string buffer_shrink_threshold("buffer-shrink-threshold");
2525 const std::string max_reliable_payload_size("max-payload-size-reliable");
2526 const std::string max_unreliable_payload_size("max-payload-size-unreliable");
2527 try {
2528 for (const auto& s : { max_local_payload_size,
2529 max_reliable_payload_size, max_unreliable_payload_size }) {
2530 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(s)) {
2531 const std::string size_str(_element.tree_.get_child(s).data());
2532 try {
2533 // add 16 Byte for the SOME/IP header
2534 const std::uint32_t its_size = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(
2535 std::stoul(size_str.c_str(), NULL, 10) + 16);
2536 if (s == max_local_payload_size) {
2537 max_local_message_size_ = its_size;
2538 } else if (s == max_reliable_payload_size) {
2539 max_reliable_message_size_ = its_size;
2540 } else if (s == max_unreliable_payload_size) {
2541 max_unreliable_message_size_ = its_size;
2542 }
2543 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
2544 VSOMEIP_ERROR<< __func__ << ": " << s << " " << e.what();
2545 }
2546 }
2547 }
2548
2549 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(buffer_shrink_threshold)) {
2550 auto bst = _element.tree_.get_child(buffer_shrink_threshold);
2551 std::string s(bst.data());
2552 try {
2553 buffer_shrink_threshold_ = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(
2554 std::stoul(s.c_str(), NULL, 10));
2555 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
2556 VSOMEIP_ERROR<< __func__ << ": " << buffer_shrink_threshold
2557 << " " << e.what();
2558 }
2559 }
2560 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(payload_sizes)) {
2561 const std::string unicast("unicast");
2562 const std::string ports("ports");
2563 const std::string port("port");
2564 const std::string max_payload_size("max-payload-size");
2565 auto its_ps = _element.tree_.get_child(payload_sizes);
2566 for (auto i = its_ps.begin(); i != its_ps.end(); ++i) {
2567 if (!i->second.get_child_optional(unicast)
2568 || !i->second.get_child_optional(ports)) {
2569 continue;
2570 }
2571 std::string its_unicast(i->second.get_child(unicast).data());
2572 for (auto j = i->second.get_child(ports).begin();
2573 j != i->second.get_child(ports).end(); ++j) {
2574
2575 if (!j->second.get_child_optional(port)
2576 || !j->second.get_child_optional(max_payload_size)) {
2577 continue;
2578 }
2579
2580 std::uint16_t its_port = ILLEGAL_PORT;
2581 std::uint32_t its_message_size = 0;
2582
2583 try {
2584 std::string p(j->second.get_child(port).data());
2585 its_port = static_cast<std::uint16_t>(std::stoul(p.c_str(),
2586 NULL, 10));
2587 std::string s(j->second.get_child(max_payload_size).data());
2588 // add 16 Byte for the SOME/IP header
2589 its_message_size = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(
2590 std::stoul(s.c_str(), NULL, 10) + 16);
2591 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
2592 VSOMEIP_ERROR << __func__ << ":" << e.what();
2593 }
2594
2595 if (its_port == ILLEGAL_PORT || its_message_size == 0) {
2596 continue;
2597 }
2598 if (max_configured_message_size_ < its_message_size) {
2599 max_configured_message_size_ = its_message_size;
2600 }
2601
2602 message_sizes_[its_unicast][its_port] = its_message_size;
2603 }
2604 }
2605 if (max_local_message_size_ != 0
2606 && max_configured_message_size_ != 0
2607 && max_configured_message_size_ > max_local_message_size_) {
2608 VSOMEIP_WARNING << max_local_payload_size
2609 << " is configured smaller than the biggest payloadsize"
2610 << " for external communication. "
2611 << max_local_payload_size << " will be increased to "
2612 << max_configured_message_size_ - 16 << " to ensure "
2613 << "local message distribution.";
2614 max_local_message_size_ = max_configured_message_size_;
2615 }
2616 if (max_local_message_size_ != 0
2617 && max_reliable_message_size_ != 0
2618 && max_reliable_message_size_ > max_local_message_size_) {
2619 VSOMEIP_WARNING << max_local_payload_size << " ("
2620 << max_local_message_size_ - 16 << ") is configured"
2621 << " smaller than " << max_reliable_payload_size << " ("
2622 << max_reliable_message_size_ - 16 << "). "
2623 << max_local_payload_size << " will be increased to "
2624 << max_reliable_message_size_ - 16 << " to ensure "
2625 << "local message distribution.";
2626 max_local_message_size_ = max_reliable_message_size_;
2627 }
2628 if (max_local_message_size_ != 0
2629 && max_unreliable_message_size_ != 0
2630 && max_unreliable_message_size_ > max_local_message_size_) {
2631 VSOMEIP_WARNING << max_local_payload_size << " ("
2632 << max_local_message_size_ - 16 << ") is configured"
2633 << " smaller than " << max_unreliable_payload_size << " ("
2634 << max_unreliable_message_size_ - 16 << "). "
2635 << max_local_payload_size << " will be increased to "
2636 << max_unreliable_message_size_ - 16 << " to ensure "
2637 << "local message distribution.";
2638 max_local_message_size_ = max_unreliable_message_size_;
2639 }
2640 }
2641 } catch (...) {
2642 }
2643}

2682 is_configured_[ET_SECURITY_AUDIT_MODE] = true;

2685
2686 auto its_remote_access = its_security->get_child_optional("allow_remote_clients");
2687 if (its_remote_access) {
2688 if (is_configured_[ET_SECURITY_REMOTE_ACCESS]) {
2689 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for security audit mode ("

2693 is_remote_access_allowed_ = (its_remote_access->data() == "true");
2694 is_configured_[ET_SECURITY_REMOTE_ACCESS] = true;
2695 }
2696 }
2697 }
2698
2699 } catch (...) {
2700 }
2701
2702#ifndef VSOMEIP_DISABLE_SECURITY
2703 if (!is_security_external())
2704 policy_manager_impl::get()->load(_element);
2705#endif // !VSOMEIP_DISABLE_SECURITY
2706}

2733
2734void
2735configuration_impl::load_partition(const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
2736
2737 static partition_id_t its_partition_id(VSOMEIP_DEFAULT_PARTITION_ID);
2738
2739 try {
2740
2741 std::stringstream its_converter;
2742 std::map<service_t, std::set<instance_t> > its_partition_members;
2743
2744 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
2745 service_t its_service(0x0);
2746 instance_t its_instance(0x0);
2747 std::string its_service_s, its_instance_s;
2748
2749 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
2750 std::string its_key(j->first);
2751 std::string its_data(j->second.data());
2752
2753 its_converter.str("");
2754 its_converter.clear();
2755
2756 if (its_data.find("0x") != std::string::npos)
2757 its_converter << std::hex;
2758 else
2759 its_converter << std::dec;
2760 its_converter << its_data;
2761
2762 if (its_key == "service") {
2763 its_converter >> its_service;
2764 its_service_s = its_data;
2765 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
2766 its_converter >> its_instance;
2767 its_instance_s = its_data;
2768 }
2769 }
2770
2771 if (its_service > 0 && its_instance > 0)
2772 its_partition_members[its_service].insert(its_instance);
2773 else
2774 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "P: <" << its_service_s << "."
2775 << its_instance_s << "> is no valid service instance.";
2776
2777 }
2778
2779 if (!its_partition_members.empty()) {
2780 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(partitions_mutex_);
2781 its_partition_id++;
2782
2783 std::stringstream its_log;
2784 its_log << "P"
2785 << std::dec << static_cast<int>(its_partition_id)
2786 << " [";
2787
2788 for (const auto &p : its_partition_members) {
2789 for (const auto &m : p.second) {
2790 partitions_[p.first][m] = its_partition_id;
2791 its_log << "<"
2792 << std::setfill('0') << std::hex
2793 << std::setw(4) << p.first << "."
2794 << std::setw(4) << m
2795 << ">";
2796 }
2797 }
2798
2799 its_log << "]";
2800 VSOMEIP_INFO << its_log.str();
2801 }
2802 } catch (...) {
2803 }
2804}
