2941
2942void configuration_impl::get_configured_timing_requests(
2943 service_t _service, const std::string &_ip_target,
2944 std::uint16_t _port_target, method_t _method,
2945 std::chrono::nanoseconds *_debounce_time,
2946 std::chrono::nanoseconds *_max_retention_time) const {
2947
2948 if (_debounce_time == nullptr || _max_retention_time == nullptr) {
2949 return;
2950 }
2951
2952 auto its_service = find_service(_service, _ip_target, _port_target);
2953 if (its_service) {
2954 auto find_method = its_service->debounce_times_requests_.find(_method);
2955 if (find_method != its_service->debounce_times_requests_.end()) {
2956 *_debounce_time = find_method->second[0];
2957 *_max_retention_time = find_method->second[1];
2958 return;
2959 }
2960 }
2961
2962 *_debounce_time = npdu_default_debounce_requ_;
2963 *_max_retention_time = npdu_default_max_retention_requ_;
2964}
2965
2966void configuration_impl::get_configured_timing_responses(
2967 service_t _service, const std::string &_ip_service,
2968 std::uint16_t _port_service, method_t _method,
2969 std::chrono::nanoseconds *_debounce_time,
2970 std::chrono::nanoseconds *_max_retention_time) const {
2971 if (_debounce_time == nullptr || _max_retention_time == nullptr) {
2972 return;
2973 }
2974
2975 auto its_service = find_service(_service, _ip_service, _port_service);
2976 if (its_service) {
2977 auto find_method = its_service->debounce_times_responses_.find(_method);
2978 if (find_method != its_service->debounce_times_responses_.end()) {
2979 *_debounce_time = find_method->second[0];
2980 *_max_retention_time = find_method->second[1];
2981 return;
2982 }
2983 }
2984
2985 *_debounce_time = npdu_default_debounce_resp_;
2986 *_max_retention_time = npdu_default_max_retention_resp_;

2998bool configuration_impl::get_client_port(
2999 service_t _service, instance_t _instance,
3000 uint16_t _remote_port, bool _reliable,
3001 std::map<bool, std::set<uint16_t> > &_used_client_ports,
3002 uint16_t &_client_port) const {
3003 bool is_configured(false);
3004 _client_port = ILLEGAL_PORT;
3005
3006 uint16_t its_specific_port(ILLEGAL_PORT);
3007 if (find_specific_port(its_specific_port, _service, _instance, _reliable, _used_client_ports)) {
3008 is_configured = true;
3009 if (its_specific_port != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
3010 _client_port = its_specific_port;
3011 return true;
3012 }
3013 }
3014
3015 // No specific port configuration found, use generic configuration
3016 uint16_t its_port(ILLEGAL_PORT);
3017 if (find_port(its_port, _remote_port, _reliable, _used_client_ports)) {
3018 is_configured = true;
3019 if (its_port != ILLEGAL_PORT) {
3020 _client_port = its_port;
3021 return true;
3022 }
3023 }
3024
3025 if (!is_configured) {
3026 // Neither specific not generic configurarion available,
3027 // use dynamic port configuration!
3028 _client_port = 0;
3029 return true;
3030 }
3031
3032 // Configured ports do exist, but they are all in use
3033 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "Cannot find free client port for communication to service ["
3034 << std::hex << std::setw(4) << std::setfill('0') << _service << "."
3035 << std::hex << std::setw(4) << std::setfill('0') << _instance << "."
3036 << std::dec << _remote_port << "."
3037 << std::boolalpha <<_reliable << "]";
3038
3039 return false;
3040}

3215bool configuration_impl::is_mandatory(const std::string &_name) const {
3216 std::set<std::string> its_candidates;
3217 for (const auto& m : mandatory_) {
3218 if (m.size() <= _name.size()) {
3219 its_candidates.insert(m);
3220 }

3222
3223 if (its_candidates.empty())
3224 return false;

3235void configuration_impl::set_mandatory(const std::string &_input) {
3236 if (_input.length() > 0) {
3237 auto found_separator = _input.find(',');
3238 std::string its_mandatory_file = _input.substr(0, found_separator);
3239 trim(its_mandatory_file);
3240 mandatory_.insert(its_mandatory_file);
3241 while (found_separator != std::string::npos) {
3242 auto last_separator = found_separator+1;
3243 found_separator = _input.find(',', last_separator);
3244 its_mandatory_file
3245 = _input.substr(last_separator, found_separator - last_separator);
3246 trim(its_mandatory_file);
3247 mandatory_.insert(its_mandatory_file);
3248 }
3249 }

3252void configuration_impl::trim(std::string &_s) {

3254 _s.begin(),
3255 std::find_if(
3256 _s.begin(),
3257 _s.end(),
3258 [](unsigned char ch) { return !std::isspace(ch); }
3259 )
3260 );
3261
3262 _s.erase(
3263 std::find_if(
3264 _s.rbegin(),
3265 _s.rend(),
3266 [](unsigned char ch) { return !std::isspace(ch); }).base(),
3267 _s.end()
3268 );

3341
3342bool configuration_impl::find_port(uint16_t &_port, uint16_t _remote, bool _reliable,
3343 std::map<bool, std::set<uint16_t> > &_used_client_ports) const {
3344 bool is_configured(false);
3345 std::list<std::shared_ptr<client>>::const_iterator it;
3346
3347 for (it = clients_.begin(); it != clients_.end(); ++it) {
3348 if (_remote != ILLEGAL_PORT && is_in_port_range(_remote,
3349 (*it)->remote_ports_[_reliable])) {
3350 is_configured = true;
3351 uint16_t its_port(ILLEGAL_PORT);
3352 if ((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable] != ILLEGAL_PORT &&
3353 is_in_port_range(((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable]),
3354 (*it)->client_ports_[_reliable])) {
3355 its_port = ++((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable]);
3356 ((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable])++;
3357 } else {
3358 ((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable])++;
3359 // on initial start of port search
3360 if ((*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable] == ILLEGAL_PORT) {
3361 its_port = (*it)->client_ports_[_reliable].first;
3362 } else {
3363 continue;
3364 }
3365 }
3366 while (its_port <= (*it)->client_ports_[_reliable].second) {
3367 if (_used_client_ports[_reliable].find(its_port)
3368 == _used_client_ports[_reliable].end()) {
3369 _port = its_port;
3370 (*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable] = its_port;
3371 return true;
3372 }
3373 its_port++;
3374 }
3375 }
3376 }
3377 // no free port was found in _used_client_ports or last_used_port
3378 // cannot be incremented for any client port range
3379 // -> reset last used port for all available client port ranges
3380 for (it = clients_.begin(); it != clients_.end(); ++it) {
3381 if (_remote != ILLEGAL_PORT && is_in_port_range(_remote,
3382 (*it)->remote_ports_[_reliable])) {
3383 (*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
3384 }
3385 }
3386 // ensure that all configured client ports are checked from beginning
3387 for (it = clients_.begin(); it != clients_.end(); ++it) {
3388 if (_remote != ILLEGAL_PORT && is_in_port_range(_remote,
3389 (*it)->remote_ports_[_reliable])) {
3390 uint16_t its_port(ILLEGAL_PORT);
3391 its_port = (*it)->client_ports_[_reliable].first;
3392 while (its_port <= (*it)->client_ports_[_reliable].second) {
3393 if (_used_client_ports[_reliable].find(its_port)
3394 == _used_client_ports[_reliable].end()) {
3395 _port = its_port;
3396 (*it)->last_used_client_port_[_reliable] = its_port;
3397 return true;
3398 }
3399 its_port++;
3400 }
3401 }
3402 }
3403 return is_configured;
3404}
3405
3406bool configuration_impl::find_specific_port(uint16_t &_port, service_t _service,
3407 instance_t _instance, bool _reliable,
3408 std::map<bool, std::set<uint16_t> > &_used_client_ports) const {
3409 bool is_configured(false);
3410 bool check_all(false);
3411 std::list<std::shared_ptr<client>>::const_iterator it;
3412 auto its_client = find_client(_service, _instance);
3413
3414 // Check for service, instance specific port configuration
3415 if (its_client && !its_client->ports_[_reliable].empty()) {
3416 is_configured = true;
3417 std::set<uint16_t>::const_iterator it;
3418 if (its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[_reliable] == ILLEGAL_PORT) {
3419 it = its_client->ports_[_reliable].begin();
3420 } else {
3421 it = its_client->ports_[_reliable].find(
3422 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[_reliable]);
3423 auto it_next = std::next(it, 1);
3424 if (it_next != its_client->ports_[_reliable].end()) {
3425 check_all = true;
3426 it = it_next;
3427 } else {
3428 it = its_client->ports_[_reliable].begin();
3429 }
3430 }
3431 while (it != its_client->ports_[_reliable].end()) {
3432 if (_used_client_ports[_reliable].find(*it)
3433 == _used_client_ports[_reliable].end()) {
3434 _port = *it;
3435 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[_reliable] = *it;
3436 VSOMEIP_INFO << "configuration_impl:find_specific_port #1:"
3437 << " service: " << std::hex << _service
3438 << " instance: " << _instance
3439 << " reliable: " << std::dec << _reliable
3440 << " return specific port: " << (uint32_t)_port;
3441 return true;
3442 }
3443 ++it;
3444 }
3445 if (check_all) {
3446 // no free port was found
3447 // ensure that all configured client ports are checked from beginning
3448 for (auto its_port : _used_client_ports[_reliable]) {
3449 if (_used_client_ports[_reliable].find(its_port)
3450 == _used_client_ports[_reliable].end()) {
3451 _port = its_port;
3452 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[_reliable] = its_port;
3453 VSOMEIP_INFO << "configuration_impl:find_specific_port #2:"
3454 << " service: " << std::hex << _service
3455 << " instance: " << _instance
3456 << " reliable: " << std::dec << _reliable
3457 << " return specific port: " << (uint32_t)_port;
3458 return true;
3459 }
3460 }
3461 }
3462 its_client->last_used_specific_client_port_[_reliable] = ILLEGAL_PORT;
3463 }
3464 return is_configured;
3465}

3555std::uint32_t configuration_impl::get_max_message_size_local() const {
3556 if (max_local_message_size_ == 0
3557 && (VSOMEIP_MAX_LOCAL_MESSAGE_SIZE == 0
3558 || VSOMEIP_MAX_TCP_MESSAGE_SIZE == 0)) {
3559 // no limit specified in configuration file and
3560 // defines are set to unlimited
3561 return MESSAGE_SIZE_UNLIMITED;
3562 }
3563
3564 uint32_t its_max_message_size = max_local_message_size_;
3565 if (VSOMEIP_MAX_TCP_MESSAGE_SIZE >= its_max_message_size) {
3566 its_max_message_size = VSOMEIP_MAX_TCP_MESSAGE_SIZE;
3567 }
3568 if (VSOMEIP_MAX_UDP_MESSAGE_SIZE > its_max_message_size) {
3569 its_max_message_size = VSOMEIP_MAX_UDP_MESSAGE_SIZE;
3570 }
3571 if (its_max_message_size < max_configured_message_size_) {
3572 its_max_message_size = max_configured_message_size_;
3573 }
3574
3575 // add sizes of the the routing_manager_proxy's messages
3576 // to the routing_manager stub
3577 return std::uint32_t(its_max_message_size + protocol::SEND_COMMAND_HEADER_SIZE);
3578}
3579
3580std::uint32_t configuration_impl::get_max_message_size_reliable(
3581 const std::string& _address, std::uint16_t _port) const {
3582 const auto its_address = message_sizes_.find(_address);
3583 if(its_address != message_sizes_.end()) {
3584 const auto its_port = its_address->second.find(_port);
3585 if(its_port != its_address->second.end()) {
3586 return its_port->second;
3587 }
3588 }

3733 return;

3759void configuration_impl::load_e2e_protected(const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
3760
3761 std::string variant("");
3762 std::string profile("");
3763 service_t service_id(0);
3764 event_t event_id(0);
3765
3766 e2e::custom_parameters_t custom_parameters;
3767
3768 for (auto l = _tree.begin(); l != _tree.end(); ++l) {
3769 std::stringstream its_converter;
3770 if (l->first == "service_id") {
3771 std::string value = l->second.data();
3772 if (value.size() > 1 && value[0] == '0' && value[1] == 'x') {
3773 its_converter << std::hex << value;
3774 } else {
3775 its_converter << std::dec << value;
3776 }
3777 its_converter >> service_id;
3778 } else if (l->first == "event_id") {
3779 std::string value = l->second.data();
3780 if (value.size() > 1 && value[0] == '0' && value[1] == 'x') {
3781 its_converter << std::hex << value;
3782 } else {
3783 its_converter << std::dec << value;
3784 }
3785 its_converter >> event_id;
3786 } else if (l->first == "variant") {
3787 std::string value = l->second.data();
3788 its_converter << value;
3789 its_converter >> variant;
3790 } else if (l->first == "profile") {
3791 std::string value = l->second.data();
3792 its_converter << value;
3793 its_converter >> profile;
3794 } else {
3795 custom_parameters[l->first.data()] = l->second.data();
3796 }
3797 }
3798 e2e_configuration_[std::make_pair(service_id, event_id)] = std::make_shared<cfg::e2e>(
3799 variant,
3800 profile,
3801 service_id,
3802 event_id,
3803 std::move(custom_parameters)
3804 );

3827void configuration_impl::load_ttl_factors(
3828 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree, ttl_map_t* _target) {
3829 const service_t ILLEGAL_VALUE(0xffff);
3830 for (const auto& i : _tree) {
3831 service_t its_service(ILLEGAL_VALUE);
3832 instance_t its_instance(ILLEGAL_VALUE);
3833 configuration::ttl_factor_t its_ttl_factor(0);
3834
3835 for (const auto& j : i.second) {
3836 std::string its_key(j.first);
3837 std::string its_value(j.second.data());
3838 std::stringstream its_converter;
3839
3840 if (its_key == "ttl_factor") {
3841 its_converter << its_value;
3842 its_converter >> its_ttl_factor;
3843 } else {
3844 // Trim "its_value"
3845 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
3846 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
3847 } else {
3848 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
3849 }
3850
3851 if (its_key == "service") {
3852 its_converter >> its_service;
3853 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
3854 its_converter >> its_instance;
3855 }
3856 }
3857 }
3858 if (its_service != ILLEGAL_VALUE
3859 && its_instance != ILLEGAL_VALUE
3860 && its_ttl_factor > 0) {
3861 (*_target)[its_service][its_instance] = its_ttl_factor;
3862 } else {
3863 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "Invalid ttl factor configuration";
3864 }
3865 }
3866}

3895configuration_impl::load_endpoint_queue_sizes(const configuration_element &_element) {

3898 const std::string endpoint_queue_limit_local("endpoint-queue-limit-local");
3899
3900 try {
3901 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(endpoint_queue_limit_external)) {
3902 if (is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMIT_EXTERNAL]) {
3903 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for "
3904 << endpoint_queue_limit_external
3905 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
3906 } else {
3907 is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMIT_EXTERNAL] = true;
3908 auto mpsl = _element.tree_.get_child(
3909 endpoint_queue_limit_external);
3910 std::string s(mpsl.data());
3911 try {
3912 endpoint_queue_limit_external_ =
3913 static_cast<configuration::endpoint_queue_limit_t>(std::stoul(
3914 s.c_str(), NULL, 10));
3915 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
3916 VSOMEIP_ERROR<<__func__ << ": " << endpoint_queue_limit_external
3917 << " " << e.what();
3918 }
3919 }
3920 }
3921 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(endpoint_queue_limit_local)) {
3922 if (is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMIT_LOCAL]) {
3923 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for "
3924 << endpoint_queue_limit_local
3925 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
3926 } else {
3927 is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMIT_LOCAL] = true;
3928 auto mpsl = _element.tree_.get_child(endpoint_queue_limit_local);
3929 std::string s(mpsl.data());
3930 try {
3931 endpoint_queue_limit_local_=
3932 static_cast<configuration::endpoint_queue_limit_t>(
3933 std::stoul(s.c_str(), NULL, 10));
3934 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
3935 VSOMEIP_ERROR<< __func__ << ": "<< endpoint_queue_limit_local
3936 << " " << e.what();
3937 }
3938 }
3939 }
3940
3941 if (_element.tree_.get_child_optional(endpoint_queue_limits)) {
3942 if (is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMITS]) {
3943 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "Multiple definitions for "
3944 << endpoint_queue_limits
3945 << " Ignoring definition from " << _element.name_;
3946 } else {
3947 is_configured_[ET_ENDPOINT_QUEUE_LIMITS] = true;
3948 const std::string unicast("unicast");
3949 const std::string ports("ports");
3950 const std::string port("port");
3951 const std::string queue_size_limit("queue-size-limit");
3952
3953 for (const auto& i : _element.tree_.get_child(endpoint_queue_limits)) {
3954 if (!i.second.get_child_optional(unicast)
3955 || !i.second.get_child_optional(ports)) {
3956 continue;
3957 }
3958 std::string its_unicast(i.second.get_child(unicast).data());
3959 for (const auto& j : i.second.get_child(ports)) {
3960

3962 || !j.second.get_child_optional(queue_size_limit)) {
3963 continue;
3964 }

3968

3970 std::string p(j.second.get_child(port).data());
3971 its_port = static_cast<std::uint16_t>(std::stoul(p.c_str(),
3972 NULL, 10));
3973 std::string s(j.second.get_child(queue_size_limit).data());
3974 its_queue_size_limit = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(std::stoul(
3975 s.c_str(), NULL, 10));
3976 } catch (const std::exception &e) {
3977 VSOMEIP_ERROR << __func__ << ":" << e.what();
3978 }
3979
3980 if (its_port == ILLEGAL_PORT || its_queue_size_limit == 0) {
3981 continue;
3982 }
3983
3984 endpoint_queue_limits_[its_unicast][its_port] = its_queue_size_limit;
3985 }
3986 }
3987 }
3988 }
3989 } catch (...) {
3990 }

4004void
4005configuration_impl::load_service_debounce(
4006 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
4007 debounce_configuration_t &_debounces) {
4008
4009 service_t its_service(0);
4010 instance_t its_instance(0);
4011 std::map<event_t, std::shared_ptr<debounce_filter_impl_t>> its_debounces;
4012
4013 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
4014 std::string its_key(i->first);
4015 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
4016 std::stringstream its_converter;
4017
4018 if (its_key == "service") {
4019 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
4020 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
4021 } else {
4022 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4023 }
4024 its_converter >> its_service;
4025 } else if (its_key == "instance") {
4026 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
4027 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
4028 } else {
4029 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4030 }
4031 its_converter >> its_instance;
4032 } else if (its_key == "events") {
4033 load_events_debounce(i->second, its_debounces);
4034 }
4035 }
4036
4037 // TODO: Improve error handling!
4038 if (its_service > 0 && its_instance > 0 && !its_debounces.empty()) {
4039 auto find_service = debounces_.find(its_service);
4040 if (find_service != debounces_.end()) {
4041 auto find_instance = find_service->second.find(its_instance);
4042 if (find_instance != find_service->second.end()) {
4043 VSOMEIP_ERROR << "Multiple debounce configurations for service "
4044 << std::hex << std::setfill('0')
4045 << std::setw(4) << its_service << "."
4046 << std::setw(4) << its_instance;
4047 return;
4048 }
4049 }
4050 _debounces[its_service][its_instance] = its_debounces;
4051 }

4064void
4065configuration_impl::load_event_debounce(
4066 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
4067 std::map<event_t, std::shared_ptr<debounce_filter_impl_t> > &_debounces) {
4068
4069 event_t its_event(0);
4070 auto its_debounce = std::make_shared<debounce_filter_impl_t>();
4071
4072 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
4073 std::string its_key(i->first);
4074 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
4075 std::stringstream its_converter;
4076
4077 if (its_key == "event") {
4078 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {
4079 its_converter << std::hex << its_value;
4080 } else {
4081 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4082 }
4083 its_converter >> its_event;
4084 } else if (its_key == "on_change") {
4085 its_debounce->on_change_ = (its_value == "true");
4086 } else if (its_key == "on_change_resets_interval") {
4087 its_debounce->on_change_resets_interval_ = (its_value == "true");
4088 } else if (its_key == "ignore") {
4089 load_event_debounce_ignore(i->second, its_debounce->ignore_);
4090 } else if (its_key == "interval") {
4091 if (its_value == "never") {
4092 its_debounce->interval_ = -1;
4093 } else {
4094 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4095 its_converter >> its_debounce->interval_;
4096 }
4097 } else if (its_key == "send_current_value_after") {
4098 its_debounce->send_current_value_after_ = (its_value == "true");
4099 }
4100 }
4101
4102 // TODO: Improve error handling
4103 if (its_event > 0) {
4104 auto find_event = _debounces.find(its_event);
4105 if (find_event == _debounces.end()) {
4106 _debounces[its_event] = its_debounce;
4107 }
4108 }

4110
4111void configuration_impl::load_event_debounce_ignore(
4112 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree,
4113 std::map<std::size_t, byte_t> &_ignore) {
4114 std::size_t its_ignored;
4115 byte_t its_mask;
4116 std::stringstream its_converter;
4117
4118 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
4119 std::string its_value = i->second.data();
4120
4121 its_mask = 0xff;
4122
4123 if (!its_value.empty()
4124 && std::find_if(its_value.begin(), its_value.end(),
4125 [](char _c) { return !std::isdigit(_c); })
4126 == its_value.end()) {
4127 its_converter.str("");
4128 its_converter.clear();
4129 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4130 its_converter >> its_ignored;
4131
4132 } else {
4133 for (auto j = i->second.begin(); j != i->second.end(); ++j) {
4134 std::string its_ignore_key(j->first);
4135 std::string its_ignore_value(j->second.data());
4136
4137 if (its_ignore_key == "index") {
4138 its_converter.str("");
4139 its_converter.clear();
4140 its_converter << std::dec << its_ignore_value;
4141 its_converter >> its_ignored;
4142 } else if (its_ignore_key == "mask") {
4143 its_converter.str("");
4144 its_converter.clear();
4145
4146 int its_tmp_mask;
4147 its_converter << std::hex << its_ignore_value;
4148 its_converter >> its_tmp_mask;
4149
4150 its_mask = static_cast<byte_t>(its_tmp_mask);
4151 }
4152 }
4153 }
4154
4155 _ignore[its_ignored] = its_mask;
4156 }

4183
4184void
4185configuration_impl::load_acceptance_data(
4186 const boost::property_tree::ptree &_tree) {
4187
4188 std::stringstream its_converter;
4189 try {
4190 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(sd_acceptance_required_ips_mutex_);
4191
4192 boost::asio::ip::address its_address;
4193 std::string its_path;
4194 std::map<bool,
4195 std::pair<boost::icl::interval_set<std::uint16_t>,
4196 boost::icl::interval_set<std::uint16_t>
4197 >
4198 > its_ports;
4199 bool has_optional, has_secure, is_reliable;
4200
4201 for (auto i = _tree.begin(); i != _tree.end(); ++i) {
4202
4203 std::string its_key(i->first);
4204 std::string its_value(i->second.data());
4205
4206 if (its_key == "address") {
4207 its_address = boost::asio::ip::address::from_string(its_value);
4208 } else if (its_key == "path") {
4209 its_path = its_value;
4210 } else if (its_key == "reliable" || its_key == "unreliable") {
4211
4212 is_reliable = (its_key == "reliable");
4213 has_optional = has_secure = false;
4214
4215 for (const auto &p : i->second) {
4216 if (p.second.size()) { // range
4217 std::uint16_t its_first(0);
4218 std::uint16_t its_last(0);
4219 port_type_e its_type(port_type_e::PT_OPTIONAL);
4220
4221 for (const auto& range : p.second) {
4222 const std::string its_key(range.first);
4223 const std::string its_value(range.second.data());
4224 if (its_key == "first" || its_key == "last" || its_key == "port") {
4225 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4226 std::uint16_t its_port_value(0);
4227 its_converter >> its_port_value;
4228 its_converter.str("");
4229 its_converter.clear();
4230 if (its_key == "first") {
4231 its_first = its_port_value;
4232 } else if (its_key == "last") {
4233 its_last = its_port_value;
4234 } else if (its_key == "port") {
4235 its_first = its_last = its_port_value;
4236 }
4237 } else if (its_key == "type") {
4238 if (its_value == "secure") {
4239 its_type = port_type_e::PT_SECURE;
4240 } else if (its_value == "optional") {
4241 its_type = port_type_e::PT_OPTIONAL;
4242 } else {
4243 its_type = port_type_e::PT_UNKNOWN;
4244 }
4245 }
4246 }
4247 if (its_type != port_type_e::PT_UNKNOWN) {
4248 if (its_type == port_type_e::PT_OPTIONAL) {
4249 has_optional = true;
4250 if (its_first != 0 && its_last != 0) {
4251 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).first.insert(
4252 boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(its_first, its_last));
4253 }
4254 } else {
4255 has_secure = true;
4256 if (its_first != 0 && its_last != 0) {
4257 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).second.insert(
4258 boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(its_first, its_last));
4259 }
4260 }
4261 }
4262 }
4263 }
4264
4265 // If optional was not set, use default!
4266 if (!has_optional) {
4267 const auto its_optional_client = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30491, 30499);
4268 const auto its_optional_client_spare = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30898, 30998);
4269 const auto its_optional_server = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30501, 30599);
4270
4271 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).first.insert(its_optional_client);
4272 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).first.insert(its_optional_client_spare);
4273 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).first.insert(its_optional_server);
4274 }
4275
4276 // If secure was not set, use default!
4277 if (!has_secure) {
4278 const auto its_secure_client = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32491, 32499);
4279 const auto its_secure_client_spare = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32898, 32998);
4280 const auto its_secure_server = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32501, 32599);
4281
4282 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).second.insert(its_secure_client);
4283 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).second.insert(its_secure_client_spare);
4284 its_ports.operator [](is_reliable).second.insert(its_secure_server);
4285 }
4286 }
4287 }
4288
4289 if (!its_address.is_unspecified()) {
4290 sd_acceptance_rules_[its_address] = std::make_pair(its_path, its_ports);
4291 }
4292 } catch (...) {
4293 // intentionally left empty
4294 }
4295}

4398 uint32_t its_separation_time(0);
4399
4400 const std::string its_value(method.second.data());

4428 its_converter >> its_separation_time;
4429 its_separation_time *= std::uint32_t(1000);

4431 }
4432 its_converter.str("");
4433 its_converter.clear();
4434 }
4435 } else {
4436 if (its_value.size() > 1 && its_value[0] == '0' && its_value[1] == 'x') {

4438 } else {
4439 its_converter << std::dec << its_value;
4440 }
4441 its_converter >> its_method;
4442 its_converter.str("");
4443 its_converter.clear();
4444 }
4445
4446 if (its_method != 0) {
4447 if (_is_request) {

4449 if (its_entry == _service->tp_client_config_.end()) {
4450 _service->tp_client_config_[its_method]
4451 = std::make_pair(its_max_segment_length, its_separation_time);

4454 << std::hex << std::setfill('0')
4455 << std::setw(4) << _service->service_ << "."
4456 << std::setw(4) << _service->instance_ << "."
4457 << std::setw(4) << its_method << "]:"
4458 << " using (" << std::dec
4459 << its_entry->second.first << ", "
4460 << its_entry->second.second << ")";
4461 }
4462 } else {
4463 const auto its_entry = _service->tp_service_config_.find(its_method);
4464 if (its_entry == _service->tp_service_config_.end()) {
4465 _service->tp_service_config_[its_method]
4466 = std::make_pair(its_max_segment_length, its_separation_time);
4467 } else {
4468 VSOMEIP_WARNING << "SOME/IP-TP: Multiple service configurations for method ["
4469 << std::hex << std::setfill('0')

4474 << its_entry->second.first << ", "

4559std::shared_ptr<debounce_filter_impl_t>
4560configuration_impl::get_debounce(const std::string &_name,
4561 service_t _service, instance_t _instance, event_t _event) const {
4562
4563 // Try to find application (client) specific debounce configuration
4564 auto found_application = applications_.find(_name);
4565 if (found_application != applications_.end()) {
4566 auto found_service = found_application->second.debounces_.find(_service);
4567 if (found_service != found_application->second.debounces_.end()) {
4568 auto found_instance = found_service->second.find(_instance);
4569 if (found_instance != found_service->second.end()) {
4570 auto found_event = found_instance->second.find(_event);
4571 if (found_event != found_instance->second.end()) {
4572 return found_event->second;
4573 }
4574 }
4575 }
4576 }
4577
4578 // If no application specific configuration was found, search for a
4579 // generic
4580 auto found_service = debounces_.find(_service);
4581 if (found_service != debounces_.end()) {
4582 auto found_instance = found_service->second.find(_instance);
4583 if (found_instance != found_service->second.end()) {
4584 auto found_event = found_instance->second.find(_event);
4585 if (found_event != found_instance->second.end()) {
4586 return found_event->second;
4587 }
4588 }
4589 }
4590 return nullptr;
4591}

4657bool configuration_impl::is_protected_port(
4658 const boost::asio::ip::address& _address, std::uint16_t _port,
4659 bool _reliable) const {
4660
4661 bool is_required(is_protected_device(_address));
4662
4663 if (!is_required) {
4664 return false;
4665 }
4666
4667 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(sd_acceptance_required_ips_mutex_);
4668 const auto found_address = sd_acceptance_rules_.find(_address);
4669 if (found_address != sd_acceptance_rules_.end()) {
4670 const auto found_reliability = found_address->second.second.find(_reliable);
4671 if (found_reliability != found_address->second.second.end()) {
4672 const auto its_range = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(_port, _port);
4673
4674 bool is_optional
4675 = (found_reliability->second.first.find(its_range)
4676 != found_reliability->second.first.end());
4677
4678 bool is_secure
4679 = (found_reliability->second.second.find(its_range)
4680 != found_reliability->second.second.end());
4681
4682 is_required = is_optional || is_secure;
4683 }
4684 }
4685
4686 return is_required;
4687}

4710
4711void configuration_impl::set_sd_acceptance_rule(
4712 const boost::asio::ip::address &_address,
4713 port_range_t _port_range, port_type_e _type,
4714 const std::string &_path, bool _reliable, bool _enable, bool _default) {
4715
4716 (void)_port_range;
4717 (void)_type;
4718
4719 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> its_lock(sd_acceptance_required_ips_mutex_);
4720
4721 const auto its_optional_client = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30491, 30499);
4722 const auto its_optional_client_spare = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30898, 30998);
4723 const auto its_optional_server = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(30501, 30599);
4724
4725 const auto its_secure_client = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32491, 32499);
4726 const auto its_secure_client_spare = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32898, 32998);
4727 const auto its_secure_server = boost::icl::interval<std::uint16_t>::closed(32501, 32599);
4728
4729 const bool rules_active = (sd_acceptance_rules_active_.find(_address)
4730 != sd_acceptance_rules_active_.end());
4731
4732 const auto found_address = sd_acceptance_rules_.find(_address);
4733 if (found_address != sd_acceptance_rules_.end()) {
4734 if (found_address->second.first.length() > 0
4735 && found_address->second.first != _path) {
4736 VSOMEIP_WARNING << __func__ << ": activation path for IP: "
4737 << _address << " differ: "
4738 << found_address->second.first << " vs. " << _path
4739 << " will use: " << found_address->second.first;
4740 } else {
4741 found_address->second.first = _path;
4742 }
4743 const auto found_reliability = found_address->second.second.find(_reliable);
4744 if (found_reliability != found_address->second.second.end()) {
4745 if (_enable) {
4746 // only insert full range interval if there are no other intervals
4747 // configured
4748 if (!_default ||
4749 (found_reliability->second.first.empty()
4750 && found_reliability->second.second.empty())) {
4751 found_reliability->second.first.add(its_optional_client);
4752 found_reliability->second.first.add(its_optional_client_spare);
4753 found_reliability->second.first.add(its_optional_server);
4754 found_reliability->second.second.add(its_secure_client);
4755 found_reliability->second.second.add(its_secure_client_spare);
4756 found_reliability->second.second.add(its_secure_server);
4757 if (!rules_active) {
4758 sd_acceptance_rules_active_.insert(_address);
4759 }
4760 VSOMEIP_INFO << "ipsec:acceptance:" << _address
4761 << ":" << (_reliable ? "tcp" : "udp") << ": using default ranges "
4762 << found_reliability->second.first << " "
4763 << found_reliability->second.second;
4764 } else {
4765 VSOMEIP_INFO << "ipsec:acceptance:" << _address
4766 << ":" << (_reliable ? "tcp" : "udp") << ": using configured ranges "
4767 << found_reliability->second.first << " "
4768 << found_reliability->second.second;
4769 }
4770 } else {
4771 found_reliability->second.first.erase(its_optional_client);
4772 found_reliability->second.first.erase(its_optional_client_spare);
4773 found_reliability->second.first.erase(its_optional_server);
4774 found_reliability->second.second.erase(its_secure_client);
4775 found_reliability->second.second.erase(its_secure_client_spare);
4776 found_reliability->second.second.erase(its_secure_server);
4777 if (found_reliability->second.first.empty()
4778 && found_reliability->second.second.empty()) {
4779 found_address->second.second.erase(found_reliability);
4780 if (found_address->second.second.empty()) {
4781 sd_acceptance_rules_.erase(found_address);
4782 if (rules_active) {// no more rules for IP present
4783 sd_acceptance_rules_active_.erase(_address);
4784 }
4785 }
4786 }
4787 }
4788 } else if (_enable) {
4789 boost::icl::interval_set<std::uint16_t> its_optional_default;
4790 its_optional_default.add(its_optional_client);
4791 its_optional_default.add(its_optional_client_spare);
4792 its_optional_default.add(its_optional_server);

4801 if (!rules_active) {

4803 }
4804
4805 const auto found_reliability = found_address->second.second.find(_reliable);
4806 VSOMEIP_INFO << "ipsec:acceptance:" << _address

4811 } else if (_enable) {
4812 boost::icl::interval_set<std::uint16_t> its_optional_default;
4813 its_optional_default.add(its_optional_client);
4814 its_optional_default.add(its_optional_client_spare);

4818 its_secure_default.add(its_secure_client_spare);

4820
4821 sd_acceptance_rules_.emplace(std::make_pair(_address,
4822 std::make_pair(
4823 _path,
4824 std::map<
4825 bool,
4826 std::pair<

4828 boost::icl::interval_set<std::uint16_t>

4830 >({{
4831 _reliable,
4832 std::make_pair(its_optional_default, its_secure_default)
4833 }}))));
4834 if (!rules_active) {
4835 sd_acceptance_rules_active_.insert(_address);
4836 }
4837
4838 const auto found_address = sd_acceptance_rules_.find(_address);
4839 if (found_address != sd_acceptance_rules_.end()) {
4840 const auto found_reliability = found_address->second.second.find(_reliable);
4841 if (found_reliability != found_address->second.second.end()) {
4842 VSOMEIP_INFO << "ipsec:acceptance:" << _address
